1
00:00:00,280 --> 00:00:07,000
Your fierceness, your harsh attitudes, your unwillingness to form bonds...

2
00:00:08,080 --> 00:00:11,800
And, of course, don't forget about the grumpiness.

3
00:00:12,120 --> 00:00:14,200
It’s all because of your fragility.

4
00:00:14,680 --> 00:00:18,800
Every marriage has arguments and fights, all of them.

5
00:00:19,320 --> 00:00:26,560
But the one who loves from the heart doesn’t say “it must be me,” they say “it must be them”

6
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:29,400
I said it from the beginning, that man is dangerous.

7
00:00:29,720 --> 00:00:37,720
I already had serious doubts about why he appeared in our lives. But he’s so cautious, so planned, it’s like he knows every step I will take.

8
00:00:38,120 --> 00:00:40,800
I realize that. I keep changing my path too.

9
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:48,920
Eylül.

10
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:53,280
Let go of my sister, bring her back.

11
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,320
What does this mean?

12
00:00:58,160 --> 00:00:59,720
What happened?

13
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:12,040
Look, I'm really trying to understand. Did I do something wrong to you? At least tell me that, because I don't get it. What happened?

14
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:16,176
Is it about something you experienced in your childhood? That brought you to this state.

15
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,920
Enough, Mercan.

16
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:22,160
Why are you so cold, so cruel?

17
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:28,160
Maybe you’re not as strong as you seem.

18
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:31,560
You’re just trying to protect yourself.

19
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,680
Are you hiding it because you’re embarrassed?

20
00:01:34,760 --> 00:01:36,480
They're not for me, Aslı.

21
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:37,720
They're for Mercan.

22
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:40,920
As a thank you? For Mercan?

23
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:46,720
Mercan girl’s heart is very beautiful. Know her worth, young man.

24
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:53,560
Whoever the cause is, save your anger for its owner, not for Mercan.

25
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:59,240
There’s no wall love can’t tear down, no obstacle it can’t overcome.

26
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:05,800
You’ll tear down those walls one by one with patience and love.

27
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:10,560
Don't forget these words, you'll see.

28
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,720
Thanks a lot children.

29
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:22,920
You let us to your home.

30
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,600
Hosted us.

31
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:26,160
We caused you trouble.

32
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,080
Not at all, don't say that.

33
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:29,680
You're always welcome here.

34
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:31,960
We're the same as well.

35
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:39,160
Go safely, Godspeed.

36
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:40,400
Thank you my child.

37
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:41,440
Thanks.

38
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:42,520
Thank you sonny.

39
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:45,960
We're waiting as well.

40
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:50,080
Come whenever you want to escape from the city.

41
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:52,000
Send these to us from time to time.

42
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:54,560
Let them run free from this mansion.

43
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,560
You heard aunty Güllü.

44
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:57,640
I have the authority now.

45
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:01,280
Of course we will.

46
00:04:01,281 --> 00:04:02,440
I loved there.

47
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,760
Thank you Ateş, my child.

48
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,880
You saved us from trouble in the dead of winter.

49
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:09,560
It is nothing worth mentioning.

50
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:12,400
Whenever you are in trouble, let me know.

51
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,520
Thank you, my son.

52
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,600
May Allah give you what your heart desires.

53
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:16,880
Thank you. Amen.

54
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,840
Mashallah, mashallah.

55
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:26,840
Such harmony between husband and wife

56
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,959
does not fall to everyone’s lot, children.

57
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:30,720
May Allah be with you.

58
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:40,680
Do not forget, my son.

59
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,960
Always leave the final word to your wife.

60
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,760
Do not forget.

61
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:51,800
The secret is knowing your husband well, my girl.

62
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,840
Keeping his heart content.

63
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,520
Then your word carries weight in this house.

64
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:09,560
Do not forget, I am telling you.

65
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:13,040
Women’s hearts must always be kept content.

66
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:16,720
Only then does a marriage turn into heaven.

67
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:18,760
Do not forget. Do not.

68
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:33,560
Malik.

69
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,320
Put these suitcases in the trunk, please.

70
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,760
Malik will take you home.

71
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:46,080
You have gone to trouble, my child.

72
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:48,120
We would have taken a bus from here.

73
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:48,840
Two of them.

74
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:50,240
A bus? With a car right here?

75
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,680
Would we tire you out?

76
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,000
Thank you, my girl.

77
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,640
Then let us go.

78
00:05:57,641 --> 00:06:00,079
We will leave. Stay well.

79
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,120
Thank you for everything.

80
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,320
Thank you, my dear.

81
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:05,600
Thank you.

82
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:06,960
Godspeed.

83
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,400
May Allah watch over you.

84
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,280
Thank you, Ateş, my son.

85
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:13,080
Thank you, my girl.

86
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,560
Thank you very much.

87
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,120
Goodbye.

88
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,400
Come on then. Come on, Güllü.

89
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,600
May Allah reunite you.

90
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,080
I am in the study.

91
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:34,640
Alright.

92
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:37,960
I will come shortly.

93
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,120
We need to talk.

94
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:45,560
Seeing them did me so much good.

95
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,520
They are such good people.

96
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:49,480
Truly special.

97
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:53,040
They radiate positive energy.

98
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,120
Don't you think so too?

99
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:57,480
I do.

100
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:02,160
Even a single word from them... lifts all the weight from your heart.

101
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,760
Now let us come to the real issue.

102
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,160
What is this ten o’clock business?

103
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,280
Why do I need to be at the mansion?

104
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:19,960
Come on.

105
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,360
Do not create mystery, tell me.

106
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,960
You will find out at ten.

107
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,040
Why are you poking at it?

108
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,200
Be in the room at ten.

109
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,640
Why does he not tell me?

110
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:38,720
Always mysterious behavior.

111
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:36,120
Shah.

112
00:08:37,680 --> 00:08:38,960
These are just ordinary marbles.

113
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:40,840
What does this mean?

114
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:43,280
What is this now?

115
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:49,680
Look here, Haydar.

116
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,680
If you are playing games with me…

117
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:54,040
What game? What are you talking about?

118
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:55,760
The man is openly mocking us.

119
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,280
How do you know it is him?

120
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,960
Maybe only you knew where you put it.

121
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:01,719
Do not drive me crazy.

122
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:04,760
Do I look like someone stupid enough to dry up my own source?

123
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:07,120
He is trying to pit us against each other.

124
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:11,600
He thinks he will take revenge on us.

125
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,440
But I will call him to account for.

126
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,520
Wait.

127
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,720
If so, not with brute force.

128
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:20,840
I know where to find him.

129
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:22,960
I won't wait this time.

130
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:25,320
We saw what happened last time you said wait.

131
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:26,800
He came home safe and sound.

132
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:29,400
This time will be different.

133
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,200
I know what to do.

134
00:09:31,201 --> 00:09:32,680
You just wait.

135
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,720
Where is this?

136
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:27,280
Are you looking for this?

137
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:34,920
Thanks.

138
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,560
How did you know I was looking for my watch?

139
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,840
I know you better than you think.

140
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:55,600
I think, we should invite Güllü sister more often.

141
00:10:56,680 --> 00:10:57,680
Alright.

142
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:02,400
Why are you smiling?

143
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,800
Did Uncle Durmuş give you marriage advice again?

144
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,160
Why do you care?

145
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:20,160
I thought maybe he reminded you of something you have forgotten.

146
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,440
What is it?

147
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:30,960
That you need to say yes to me.

148
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:35,799
Now when I ask why you called me at ten,

149
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:37,800
you need to answer by saying yes.

150
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,640
Apparently that is the secret of a happy marriage.

151
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,120
I am teasing you.

152
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:52,840
You did not take it seriously, I hope.

153
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,280
Yes.

154
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:58,160
You will learn tonight why I called you.

155
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,880
I followed Uncle Durmuş’s advice.

156
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,200
Satisfied?

157
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:24,280
Allah Allah.

158
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,760
Why can I not put this necklace on?

159
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:33,160
It is stubborn.

160
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:39,080
Let me help.

161
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:19,360
Thank you.

162
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:21,880
You are welcome.

163
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:25,240
I have work to do, got to go out.

164
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:55,240
Look at these.

165
00:14:58,440 --> 00:15:00,440
All from ancient times.

166
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,360
Oh Nermin Yıldırım.

167
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,640
Were you the kind of woman to fall into this state?

168
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:14,440
You used to shake the entire store at fashion houses.

169
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:17,520
Now you cannot even buy a custom evening gown.

170
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:24,120
If Haydar sold those diamonds,

171
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:26,160
I could buy myself a few things.

172
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:30,880
Always one step ahead. Always.

173
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:32,960
Who are you talking about?

174
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:35,440
Ateş?

175
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:38,160
I came back empty-handed from the deal with Nezir.

176
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:39,720
Ateş bought all the stones.

177
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:41,760
You said what?

178
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:44,440
Do something, Haydar.

179
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,400
Go get those diamonds.

180
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:49,680
How?

181
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,200
How should I know?

182
00:15:51,201 --> 00:15:52,400
Figure something out.

183
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:55,480
I am sick of this miserable life.

184
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:57,520
And these worn-out clothes.

185
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,240
No.

186
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:02,720
No, he will not give up.

187
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:08,240
He will not leave us alone until he finishes us.

188
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:10,320
But he will not reach his goal.

189
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,920
Before he finishes us, I need to cut his breath.

190
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:36,920
All done.

191
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:38,240
Would he ever escape us?

192
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,640
Do you know what kind of fortune lies in this pouch, brother?

193
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:45,160
The fortune Haydar and Nezir lost.

194
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:51,719
I wonder what Haydar and Nezir will do

195
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,560
when they find pebbles instead of diamonds.

196
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,800
No doubt they had quite a shock.

197
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:01,120
I would love to see Haydar’s face.

198
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:03,120
I should have put a camera there.

199
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,160
When you said Aslı, I got curious too.

200
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:08,720
What do we do with these?

201
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:11,080
Get rid of them.

202
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:12,480
Destroy them.

203
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,480
None of them will be touched.

204
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:21,520
Let's meet.

205
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:25,880
If you have nothing to say, I will be going.

206
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,920
No, Aslı.

207
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:36,680
You are in a good mood today.

208
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:38,680
You seem so too.

209
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,640
Do not bring your issues with Mercan into this.

210
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:45,119
I mean because of the movie night.

211
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:46,176
So there is no misunderstanding.

212
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:47,200
What happened...

213
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:50,760
I was going to talk to you about that.

214
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:54,200
We will do it tonight.

215
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:57,080
We said ten o’clock.

216
00:18:01,040 --> 00:18:02,040
Well done.

217
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,080
Did I not tell you?

218
00:18:03,360 --> 00:18:05,200
You were going to cancel in a moment of anger.

219
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:11,280
You said okay.

220
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:13,760
Accepted.

221
00:18:16,520 --> 00:18:18,120
Are you expecting applause or something?

222
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:19,960
It would not be bad actually.

223
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:21,440
You know what you should do?

224
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:23,600
Put my name in the end credits.

225
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:28,320
Alright, alright.

226
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:29,720
Everything was ready anyway.

227
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:31,080
I was waiting to hear from you.

228
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,680
Informed now.

229
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:35,880
But Mercan should stay out of sight for a while.

230
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:37,960
So the surprise does not get spoiled.

231
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:41,040
You are right. I will handle it.

232
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:45,600
Do not overdo it.

233
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:49,160
In the end, it is a simple movie screening.

234
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:51,640
When have you ever seen me overdo anything?

235
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:53,960
Always.

236
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:56,360
You're becoming literal on everything.

237
00:18:57,360 --> 00:18:58,040
Bro...

238
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:00,120
I threw a right hook, then a left...

239
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,440
That beating was enough for me.

240
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:03,280
Anyway, I will take care of these.

241
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:04,320
I am off.

242
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,040
Insallah she likes it.

243
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:16,680
She will be happy.

244
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:40,360
Here is your coffee with one sugar.

245
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:41,600
Thank you.

246
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:43,320
You always make the coffee.

247
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:44,720
Next time I will do it.

248
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:47,120
Is coffee something worth mentioning?

249
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:07,840
Hey, hey, hey.

250
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,000
Where to?

251
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:11,000
To Demet’s.

252
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,920
You really do not understand people’s moods.

253
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:16,680
Leave the kids alone for a bit.

254
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:19,840
Is there something going between them?

255
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:21,520
No.

256
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:23,759
At least not yet.

257
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,040
But it is close.

258
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,000
Unless you go and sabotage.

259
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:29,120
I cannot allow such things at the company.

260
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:30,560
Why not?

261
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,360
They are not doing anything wrong.

262
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:34,080
They are just getting to know each other.

263
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:36,760
Then they can get to know each other outside.

264
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,680
Why are you like this?

265
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:42,080
Tell me, why?

266
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:43,880
How?

267
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,440
You have let go of everything.

268
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:47,400
You think of nothing but work.

269
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:49,240
Work, work.

270
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,439
There is no love in your life.

271
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:52,640
No friendship.

272
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:53,120
Nothing.

273
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:54,200
Nothing at all.

274
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:57,240
Mind your own business, alright?

275
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:57,920
You know what they say.

276
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:59,520
They say, curiosity killed the cat.

277
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,080
Whoever said that was wrong.

278
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,360
Whoever said that was stupid.

279
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,760
Curiosity is the lifeblood of the mind.

280
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:08,040
Lifeblood?

281
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:11,520
Lifeblood.

282
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:17,120
There is a ton of work there.

283
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:18,880
There is no way

284
00:21:18,881 --> 00:21:20,000
it will be done today.

285
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:21,080
Who says?

286
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:23,519
Look at what I have handled so far.

287
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:24,640
I cannot handle this?

288
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:27,840
Bravo.

289
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:30,680
I admire your work ethic.

290
00:21:30,840 --> 00:21:32,240
Thanks again.

291
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:35,160
Enjoy.

292
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:38,440
I was going to say…

293
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:44,600
I was going to ask…

294
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:54,960
Would you like to go to a concert?

295
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,440
Again?

296
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:01,320
I want to make up for last time.

297
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:03,880
That band has not come to Turkey in a long time.

298
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,440
I would be happy if we go.

299
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:08,960
I do not know.

300
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,320
Alright, let us go.

301
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:21,800
But give me those tickets.

302
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,520
Let us not have another fiasco.

303
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,000
I cannot handle it.

304
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:26,200
Give them.

305
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:34,999
If I lose them again,

306
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,320
I would not handle it either. We would end up in hospital.

307
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,440
We will have fun.

308
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:41,400
A lot of fun.

309
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:42,840
It will be perfect.

310
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:44,440
I cannot wait.

311
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:45,520
Me too.

312
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:50,240
Did you like the coffee?

313
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:51,160
Very good.

314
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:52,520
I brewed it.

315
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:54,080
Health to your hands.

316
00:22:54,160 --> 00:22:55,160
Thank you.

317
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:20,640
Here you go, Ms. Mercan.

318
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:22,160
Thank you, Çiçek.

319
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:23,880
Enjoy.

320
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:25,640
Did Ateş tell you anything?

321
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:27,640
Any instructions?

322
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,000
No.

323
00:23:31,840 --> 00:23:32,240
Ok.

324
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:33,600
Thank you.

325
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:51,240
There is still time.

326
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:53,880
I am bursting with curiosity.

327
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:55,360
What will happen tonight?

328
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:05,480
You are ready, right?

329
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:06,640
Let's go.

330
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:10,600
Where?

331
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:11,680
To the company.

332
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:13,800
Where did this come from?

333
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:16,000
I thought we were not going.

334
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:19,040
We have a few files to handle.

335
00:24:21,280 --> 00:24:23,560
Have them email it, we can work from home.

336
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:27,440
We cannot work from home.

337
00:24:27,560 --> 00:24:30,280
I have a few other things to handle.

338
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:41,080
Do not look like that. Come on.

339
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:43,800
I'll be waiting in the car.

340
00:24:44,760 --> 00:24:46,080
Alright.

341
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:56,080
What will he do tonight?

342
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:21,640
You finally made it.

343
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:23,360
What is going on?

344
00:25:23,440 --> 00:25:24,920
Why did you call me in such a rush?

345
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:27,000
This place is close to the company.

346
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,640
Speak quickly.

347
00:25:29,120 --> 00:25:31,000
I lost a fortune today because of Ateş.

348
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:33,320
He found the stones.

349
00:25:33,321 --> 00:25:35,120
And he took them all.

350
00:25:35,920 --> 00:25:36,120
Who?

351
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:37,400
Ateş?

352
00:25:37,800 --> 00:25:38,800
Who else?

353
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:40,320
We had a deal.

354
00:25:40,760 --> 00:25:42,520
I was supposed to know every move he made.

355
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:45,000
I did not know.

356
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:46,600
Do not play games with me.

357
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:48,520
I am not playing any games.

358
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:53,320
The last thing Ateş told me was that he would find the stones and destroy them.

359
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:54,520
Destroy the stones?

360
00:25:56,120 --> 00:25:57,120
Is he insane?

361
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,839
Do you not live together?

362
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:05,880
Do you not work at the same company?

363
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:08,080
How do you not know this?

364
00:26:09,440 --> 00:26:12,080
Either you are asleep on your feet,

365
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:14,240
or you are truly playing games with me.

366
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:19,040
If it is the second… I will ruin you, Aslı.

367
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:21,880
I am telling you again.

368
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:25,560
I did not know Ateş found the stones.

369
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:28,240
And I do not understand you.

370
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:31,439
You are tearing the world apart because two stones disappeared.

371
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:34,080
You said you did not care about money.

372
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:35,760
You only wanted Mercan.

373
00:26:40,560 --> 00:26:41,560
I still do.

374
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:42,640
Ok then.

375
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,640
Forget these trivial things.

376
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:46,400
Stick to the plan.

377
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:50,480
I said I would bring you Mercan, and I will.

378
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:07,280
I will not let her be his.

379
00:27:10,040 --> 00:27:12,440
I will do whatever it takes to win her.

380
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:24,920
That couple was so sweet, was not it?

381
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:27,280
They talked with me the whole way.

382
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:28,920
Yes.

383
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:31,880
It was as if they healed everyone and left.

384
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:35,960
I have not felt this good in a long time.

385
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:37,720
Me too.

386
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:39,560
It feels like I came back to life.

387
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:41,240
Çiçek?

388
00:27:44,280 --> 00:27:46,960
I am so happy and peaceful when I am with you.

389
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:49,680
Should we talk to your mother already?

390
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:51,640
Let us get married.

391
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:54,000
I want it too.

392
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:57,800
My mother has been upset lately.

393
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:00,480
I am afraid she will react badly.

394
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:03,280
Why is Aunt Binnaz upset?

395
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:05,840
That loan shark whose debt was paid…

396
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:07,320
She is fixated on him.

397
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:09,120
She will not relax until she finds out.

398
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:16,440
Berat’s debt is my debt now.

399
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:18,800
I will pay every last penny.

400
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:21,440
Works for me.

401
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:23,240
But I warn you.

402
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:28,320
If you do not pay within two days, I will make you pay another way.

403
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:30,040
I said I will pay.

404
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:33,240
But you will stay away from Berat.

405
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:34,720
Agreed?

406
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:37,920
Agreed.

407
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:42,200
Then it is settled.

408
00:28:42,520 --> 00:28:44,560
We will talk whenever you say.

409
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:46,920
Thank you for your understanding.

410
00:28:48,280 --> 00:28:49,640
What time is it?

411
00:28:50,320 --> 00:28:52,200
My mother will be waiting.

412
00:28:52,720 --> 00:28:53,120
Alright.

413
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:54,480
Do you like cotton candy?

414
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:55,960
Very much.

415
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:58,240
Then let us get some on the way.

416
00:28:58,560 --> 00:28:59,560
Ok.

417
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:14,720
I cannot focus on work.

418
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:16,240
There is still time.

419
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:17,800
How will I last until ten?

420
00:29:18,320 --> 00:29:19,640
What is he planning?

421
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:22,879
Dinner?

422
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:24,360
No.

423
00:29:25,320 --> 00:29:26,520
A surprise, clearly.

424
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:29,880
Is it good or bad?

425
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:31,320
He gives no hint.

426
00:29:36,240 --> 00:29:37,720
I am getting too excited.

427
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:45,800
What is it?

428
00:29:47,280 --> 00:29:48,440
What?

429
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:50,720
You're smiling.

430
00:29:53,360 --> 00:29:54,360
No.

431
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:59,480
Who knows what is going through your mind?

432
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:02,800
Did you say something?

433
00:30:03,520 --> 00:30:04,520
Me?

434
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:06,720
Yes.

435
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:08,080
No.

436
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:36,960
Sorry.

437
00:30:37,680 --> 00:30:39,040
I'm not aware.

438
00:30:39,560 --> 00:30:40,640
I am.

439
00:30:44,040 --> 00:30:45,040
Of what?

440
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:46,200
That you are not aware of.

441
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:48,840
Alright, I stopped.

442
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,160
What happened now?

443
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:16,039
Sorry, I was not aware…

444
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:17,360
I know.

445
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:19,560
You are doing it without realizing.

446
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:23,320
If only I knew.

447
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:25,440
What?

448
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:29,000
What else?

449
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:31,600
Tell me what you planned for tonight.

450
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:33,640
I am dying of curiosity.

451
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:36,880
Look, I am trying to work here.

452
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:40,439
Please do not distract me.

453
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:41,520
Please.

454
00:31:47,440 --> 00:31:49,000
He is stubborn. He will not tell.

455
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:12,680
Come on, Berat.

456
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:16,720
Insallah I do not get caught.

457
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:25,000
Where is Derya?

458
00:32:33,560 --> 00:32:35,400
Allah, Insallah I do not get caught.

459
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:38,280
Holding a rose here would look strange.

460
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:15,160
Thank God, he left.

461
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:21,880
Berat. Yes?

462
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:24,440
You scared me. What are you doing there?

463
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:26,280
Maintenance.

464
00:33:27,120 --> 00:33:28,120
Since I am the gardener.

465
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:33,680
How are you?

466
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:35,320
Good, and you?

467
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:36,760
Good.

468
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:38,440
May it be easy.

469
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:38,880
Thanks.

470
00:33:39,040 --> 00:33:40,680
What is that? Are you hiding something?

471
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:43,320
No?

472
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:45,560
What's it?

473
00:33:50,840 --> 00:33:51,840
What's this?

474
00:33:54,360 --> 00:33:55,360
A red rose.

475
00:33:55,920 --> 00:33:57,480
Thorny, fragrant,

476
00:33:57,800 --> 00:33:59,080
beautiful.

477
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:01,400
I know that much. What will you do with it?

478
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:04,600
For you.

479
00:34:05,320 --> 00:34:06,320
Why?

480
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:08,280
Because...

481
00:34:09,600 --> 00:34:10,680
You're a rose as well.

482
00:34:11,440 --> 00:34:12,440
Am I?

483
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:18,200
It is beautiful.

484
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:20,320
Like you.

485
00:34:23,200 --> 00:34:24,520
It smells wonderful.

486
00:34:26,520 --> 00:34:27,520
Thank you.

487
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:28,560
You are welcome.

488
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:30,280
I will put it in a vase.

489
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:33,559
It is beautiful.

490
00:34:33,560 --> 00:34:35,360
You too.

491
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:41,520
You almost got caught, Berat.

492
00:34:58,320 --> 00:35:00,640
What will I say when I call Ateş?

493
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:04,640
It has to be convincing so he comes to the mansion immediately.

494
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:27,360
Is there a gathering at the mansion, Binnaz?

495
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:29,360
What are these preparations?

496
00:35:30,040 --> 00:35:31,680
I do not know too, Ms. Nermin.

497
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:33,760
Alright, thank you.

498
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:41,520
Why do you want to know everything?

499
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:47,240
Because I live in this mansion.

500
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:53,240
I am exposed to everything and everyone here.

501
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:56,360
For example, I walk into the living room

502
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:59,560
and see someone I never want to see.

503
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:03,559
What do I do?

504
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:07,360
I leave without even drinking my tea.

505
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:09,360
Do you leave anyone any peace?

506
00:36:15,560 --> 00:36:18,640
Let me handle that girl first, then it will be your turn.

507
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:25,480
Look at this.

508
00:36:26,240 --> 00:36:28,600
There seems to be something missing in the project drawing.

509
00:36:39,760 --> 00:36:40,760
You check it.

510
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:46,880
Yes, Mrs. Müzeyyen?

511
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:50,040
Ateş, my dear. I am calling Aslı, cannot reach her.

512
00:36:50,400 --> 00:36:52,400
If she is there, tell her to come to the mansion.

513
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:54,840
Are you alright?

514
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:55,960
You do not sound well.

515
00:36:58,280 --> 00:37:00,360
I do not feel well.

516
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:02,040
I have no strength.

517
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:03,920
My blood pressure probably dropped.

518
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:05,280
Alright.

519
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:08,640
Rest, put your feet up. I am coming.

520
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:11,120
I will tell Cemal to stay with you.

521
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:14,040
Not needed dear, do not leave your work.

522
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,200
Is it more important than you?

523
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:17,280
I am coming.

524
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:18,520
Thank you dear.

525
00:37:24,520 --> 00:37:25,679
I need to leave.

526
00:37:25,680 --> 00:37:27,040
Mrs. Müzeyyen does not feel well.

527
00:37:27,200 --> 00:37:28,200
Something serious?

528
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:31,560
Not serious, but it would be better to be there than here.

529
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:35,240
You can finish the remaining work and come.

530
00:37:36,240 --> 00:37:37,240
At ten.

531
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:39,040
Get well soon.

532
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:41,920
I will be there at ten.

533
00:37:43,440 --> 00:37:44,440
Alright.

534
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:46,840
I will wait.

535
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:52,880
At ten.

536
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:59,120
Alright... 10.

537
00:38:15,600 --> 00:38:16,600
Daha çok var.

538
00:38:24,640 --> 00:38:26,200
Allah Allah.

539
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:29,440
Where could I have drop the car key?

540
00:38:37,520 --> 00:38:38,600
Not here either.

541
00:38:43,160 --> 00:38:44,320
I must find it.

542
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:48,120
Can it be here?

543
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:59,680
Where could it be?

544
00:39:04,160 --> 00:39:06,000
Where did I put it?

545
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:08,440
Is this what you are looking for?

546
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:11,480
Bless you, Cemal Bey.

547
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:14,120
I have been looking for it for two hours.

548
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:15,520
Thank you.

549
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:16,480
What is it, Malik?

550
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:17,920
You look quite happy today?

551
00:39:17,960 --> 00:39:19,400
I am very happy, Mr. Cemal.

552
00:39:19,640 --> 00:39:21,519
So happy it feels like

553
00:39:21,520 --> 00:39:23,760
there are birds flying in my stomach.

554
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:25,959
Butterflies.

555
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:26,640
Good, good.

556
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:28,120
I am glad to see you like this.

557
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:29,840
You looked sad last time.

558
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:33,000
You know, Malik.

559
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:36,920
Sometimes the same thing is both trouble and cure for the heart.

560
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:38,920
You are right, Mr. Cemal.

561
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:40,120
Correct.

562
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:44,640
Do not lose whoever is in your heart.

563
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:45,920
May your cure never leave you.

564
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:47,240
Insallah you always smile.

565
00:39:47,560 --> 00:39:47,760
Thank you.

566
00:39:47,880 --> 00:39:49,240
I hope the same for you.

567
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:52,760
My trouble has no cure, Malik.

568
00:39:53,800 --> 00:39:58,680
They say the night is darkest when it's closest to the sun.

569
00:39:58,880 --> 00:39:59,880
You know.

570
00:40:00,120 --> 00:40:01,360
I know Malik but it's not that.

571
00:40:03,040 --> 00:40:06,440
They say the darkest hour comes before dawn.

572
00:40:07,640 --> 00:40:11,279
But when a person’s night is dark even in daylight…

573
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:13,040
there is nothing left to wait for.

574
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:15,800
Do not mind me.

575
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:16,960
I am happy for you.

576
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:22,840
Mr. Cemal, Insallah everything falls into place for you soon.

577
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:25,240
Whatever is best, Malik.

578
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:01,880
Mrs. Müzeyyen, why does Ateş need to come?

579
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:03,576
Do not be stubborn, let me take you to the hospital,

580
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:04,600
please.

581
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:07,440
I do not want to go to the hospital.

582
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:08,680
Do not insist.

583
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:10,240
Then drink your ayran at least.

584
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:27,960
How are you, Mrs. Müzeyyen?

585
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:31,320
Cemal gave me salty ayran.

586
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:33,600
I am a bit better.

587
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:36,560
I have been saying for an hour to let me take her to the hospital.

588
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:37,720
She does not want to.

589
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:39,560
Call our doctor, Cemal.

590
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:41,720
No, my son. What can he do?

591
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:44,200
You are exaggerating.

592
00:41:44,840 --> 00:41:47,320
Another salty ayran and I will be fine.

593
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:48,600
I am better.

594
00:41:49,200 --> 00:41:50,760
It's better that a doctor had seen you.

595
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:55,200
Alright. Since you are here bro, I will return to my work.

596
00:41:55,920 --> 00:41:56,920
Ok.

597
00:41:59,200 --> 00:42:01,600
Ateş, my son, call Aslı please.

598
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:03,960
I could not reach her and worried.

599
00:42:12,840 --> 00:42:13,840
Hello, Aslı?

600
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:15,200
Ateş?

601
00:42:16,040 --> 00:42:17,040
Are you ok?

602
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:19,040
Yes. I am at the company.

603
00:42:20,600 --> 00:42:22,120
Mrs. Müzeyyen called you.

604
00:42:23,560 --> 00:42:25,400
She got worried since she could not reach you.

605
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:28,400
My battery died.

606
00:42:28,640 --> 00:42:29,760
I just saw the calls.

607
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:32,120
Alright, I am giving the phone to her.

608
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:33,240
Give it, my son.

609
00:42:33,241 --> 00:42:34,640
I will check on Cemal.

610
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:36,640
Okay dear.

611
00:42:44,520 --> 00:42:47,880
Aslı, everything is going as planned.

612
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:50,280
Is Ateş there?

613
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:52,520
No, he went to Cemal.

614
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:54,320
Ok.

615
00:42:54,960 --> 00:42:57,920
I will hang up. Handle it before Ateş arrives.

616
00:42:58,800 --> 00:43:00,200
Do not worry, I will.

617
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:13,360
How are the preparations?

618
00:43:21,320 --> 00:43:22,880
I thought you would not overdo it.

619
00:43:25,800 --> 00:43:27,160
Brother, what is overdoing here?

620
00:43:29,960 --> 00:43:31,360
I only prepared a movie poster.

621
00:43:31,760 --> 00:43:32,920
That is normal.

622
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:35,400
I also spoke to the kitchen.

623
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:37,960
They will make popcorn during the movie.

624
00:43:38,080 --> 00:43:38,880
Enough already.

625
00:43:39,040 --> 00:43:40,200
No, enough to you.

626
00:43:40,560 --> 00:43:42,480
Have you ever seen a movie without popcorn?

627
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:45,240
Cinema without popcorn, is like a world without the sun.

628
00:43:46,200 --> 00:43:47,560
Drinks are ready too.

629
00:43:48,360 --> 00:43:50,959
If you had half my taste, there would be no problem.

630
00:43:50,960 --> 00:43:52,520
Every beauty has a flaw.

631
00:43:57,240 --> 00:43:58,680
Insallah she does not misunderstand.

632
00:43:58,800 --> 00:44:00,480
There is nothing to misunderstand.

633
00:44:00,680 --> 00:44:02,080
You will just watch a movie.

634
00:44:02,320 --> 00:44:03,600
It is a children’s movie.

635
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:06,496
Anyone hearing would think something else.

636
00:44:06,520 --> 00:44:08,840
I am telling you. This is the best gesture you could make.

637
00:44:11,200 --> 00:44:12,200
Thank you.

638
00:44:12,920 --> 00:44:13,920
You put in effort.

639
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:15,440
My pleasure.

640
00:44:15,600 --> 00:44:16,920
It was only a poster.

641
00:44:17,160 --> 00:44:18,680
Did we throw stones and tire our arms?

642
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:22,320
Mercan will arrive soon.

643
00:44:22,640 --> 00:44:23,760
She should not see this.

644
00:44:24,760 --> 00:44:26,240
You put in effort. It looks nice.

645
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:29,240
Thanks.

646
00:44:29,560 --> 00:44:33,280
I will go to Mrs. Müzeyyen.

647
00:45:01,120 --> 00:45:02,120
I had something come up.

648
00:45:02,920 --> 00:45:04,080
Our plan is cancelled.

649
00:45:24,680 --> 00:45:26,120
Nothing serious, right?

650
00:45:27,360 --> 00:45:30,040
Look at him pretending to care.

651
00:45:30,200 --> 00:45:31,200
Snake!

652
00:45:46,920 --> 00:45:48,200
No, nothing.

653
00:45:53,840 --> 00:45:54,840
Alright.

654
00:46:01,800 --> 00:46:03,280
Oh God...

655
00:46:04,200 --> 00:46:05,200
What happened now?

656
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:08,080
Coffee break.

657
00:46:08,680 --> 00:46:10,280
Will you buy me a coffee?

658
00:46:11,760 --> 00:46:13,040
Sure.

659
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:25,800
Two Turkish coffees, please.

660
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:47,920
How are you, Mrs. Müzeyyen?

661
00:46:48,720 --> 00:46:49,240
Fine, dear.

662
00:46:49,320 --> 00:46:51,200
Much better, thank you.

663
00:46:53,440 --> 00:46:55,480
Aslı still got some jobs to do, she'll be late.

664
00:46:56,200 --> 00:46:57,200
That's fine. I'm with you.

665
00:47:04,600 --> 00:47:05,600
Wait.

666
00:47:05,960 --> 00:47:07,840
He gave you a ten o’clock appointment, right?

667
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:09,600
And did not say what you would do.

668
00:47:10,920 --> 00:47:11,920
Yes.

669
00:47:13,160 --> 00:47:15,480
And just texted saying it was cancelled.

670
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:19,200
What is he trying to do?

671
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:23,520
Don't know.

672
00:47:25,320 --> 00:47:26,960
He seemed excited though.

673
00:47:27,720 --> 00:47:30,160
Or maybe it felt like that.

674
00:47:30,360 --> 00:47:32,400
HJe's saying come, then cancels...

675
00:47:32,560 --> 00:47:33,560
I don't understand him.

676
00:47:35,680 --> 00:47:37,160
You seem a bit disappointed.

677
00:47:40,960 --> 00:47:41,960
No.

678
00:47:42,440 --> 00:47:43,440
Why would I be?

679
00:47:43,480 --> 00:47:45,040
I was just curious.

680
00:47:52,120 --> 00:47:53,160
Your coffees.

681
00:47:54,760 --> 00:47:56,040
Thanks.

682
00:47:56,120 --> 00:47:57,120
Thank you.

683
00:48:05,320 --> 00:48:06,600
Thanks again.

684
00:48:09,720 --> 00:48:11,000
Enjoy.

685
00:48:11,480 --> 00:48:12,520
Thanks.

686
00:48:15,720 --> 00:48:17,600
So how are things with your father?

687
00:48:18,680 --> 00:48:20,040
He wants to talk.

688
00:48:21,200 --> 00:48:22,560
But I do not want to.

689
00:48:25,400 --> 00:48:27,920
I still cannot forgive him.

690
00:48:36,120 --> 00:48:37,680
Brother, what is it?

691
00:48:38,360 --> 00:48:39,360
Is there a problem?

692
00:48:40,120 --> 00:48:42,160
Sure, if I can help.

693
00:48:45,440 --> 00:48:47,000
Sure, if I can help.

694
00:48:48,880 --> 00:48:51,440
I arranged a last-minute meeting with an important investor.

695
00:48:52,440 --> 00:48:53,600
We will have dinner tonight.

696
00:48:53,640 --> 00:48:55,600
The topics fall right into your field.

697
00:48:57,480 --> 00:48:59,440
Would you come to the dinner with me?

698
00:49:02,960 --> 00:49:04,000
Dinner?

699
00:49:06,320 --> 00:49:06,840
Not sure.

700
00:49:06,920 --> 00:49:08,640
This is sudden.

701
00:49:10,320 --> 00:49:11,320
Go, dear.

702
00:49:11,520 --> 00:49:12,520
It is just dinner.

703
00:49:13,120 --> 00:49:14,200
You will come too?

704
00:49:17,480 --> 00:49:18,280
I cannot.

705
00:49:18,360 --> 00:49:20,280
I have tons of work to do here.

706
00:49:26,120 --> 00:49:27,120
What do you say?

707
00:49:30,640 --> 00:49:31,680
She will come.

708
00:49:32,040 --> 00:49:33,720
You should go, just for a change.

709
00:49:44,440 --> 00:49:45,999
Alright. I will come.

710
00:49:46,000 --> 00:49:47,760
It's for your job in the end.

711
00:49:51,160 --> 00:49:52,680
Great.

712
00:49:52,800 --> 00:49:55,480
I will call you later.

713
00:50:19,840 --> 00:50:21,200
My back is killing me.

714
00:50:25,840 --> 00:50:26,840
What happened?

715
00:50:27,640 --> 00:50:29,560
I am obsessed with this debt issue.

716
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:31,600
Who paid this debt?

717
00:50:32,200 --> 00:50:34,600
You are really obsessed now.

718
00:50:37,200 --> 00:50:38,200
Ne demek taktım?

719
00:50:39,040 --> 00:50:40,880
It is not a small amount.

720
00:50:44,000 --> 00:50:45,000
I'm curious.

721
00:50:45,560 --> 00:50:47,120
I will learn.

722
00:50:48,320 --> 00:50:49,320
How?

723
00:50:51,680 --> 00:50:54,560
I will go ask those loan sharks.

724
00:50:55,640 --> 00:50:56,680
No. I will not allow it.

725
00:50:56,800 --> 00:50:57,919
What do you mean allow?

726
00:50:57,920 --> 00:51:00,560
I do not need your permission.

727
00:51:00,920 --> 00:51:01,959
Do not be ridiculous mom.

728
00:51:01,960 --> 00:51:03,640
They are dangerous people.

729
00:51:04,560 --> 00:51:05,760
I don't care.

730
00:51:05,920 --> 00:51:06,920
Don't push me.

731
00:51:07,160 --> 00:51:07,520
I will.

732
00:51:07,680 --> 00:51:10,200
I will stand in front of them and ask who paid the debt.

733
00:51:10,800 --> 00:51:11,800
For God’s sake.

734
00:51:11,920 --> 00:51:13,280
What happened when I learned?

735
00:51:14,680 --> 00:51:15,720
You did?

736
00:51:22,440 --> 00:51:24,560
So you know who paid?

737
00:51:28,840 --> 00:51:29,800
Of course not.

738
00:51:29,801 --> 00:51:31,400
Didn't I tell if I know?

739
00:51:31,960 --> 00:51:33,400
If I knew, would I not tell you mom?

740
00:51:35,080 --> 00:51:37,040
I meant what is it matter to know.

741
00:51:37,120 --> 00:51:38,120
Berat.

742
00:51:40,040 --> 00:51:42,160
Do not twist words.

743
00:51:42,520 --> 00:51:44,280
Don't I know when you lie,

744
00:51:44,360 --> 00:51:45,480
or telling the truth?

745
00:51:46,000 --> 00:51:47,400
Tell me who paid it.

746
00:51:50,920 --> 00:51:52,279
Come on brother, say it.

747
00:51:52,280 --> 00:51:53,280
Stop dragging it out.

748
00:52:15,080 --> 00:52:16,480
Welcome.

749
00:52:16,720 --> 00:52:17,720
Here is your table.

750
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:29,960
Thank you.

751
00:52:47,120 --> 00:52:50,480
Is this place suitable for a business dinner?

752
00:52:51,840 --> 00:52:55,400
It is a bit shabby, dark.

753
00:52:55,960 --> 00:52:56,960
You are right.

754
00:52:57,200 --> 00:52:59,840
But the investors wanted it.

755
00:53:07,680 --> 00:53:09,640
Tell me about the investor.

756
00:53:09,840 --> 00:53:11,880
So I do not say something wrong.

757
00:53:12,480 --> 00:53:14,280
I do not know much either.

758
00:53:14,640 --> 00:53:15,680
It was sudden.

759
00:53:16,000 --> 00:53:20,800
We connected through a mutual contact.

760
00:53:21,080 --> 00:53:22,680
We will get to know them at dinner.

761
00:53:32,760 --> 00:53:34,080
They're late.

762
00:53:40,320 --> 00:53:42,680
Just messaged. They're stuck in the traffic.

763
00:54:23,520 --> 00:54:24,600
Clumsy me.

764
00:54:25,200 --> 00:54:26,200
No problem.

765
00:54:26,520 --> 00:54:27,520
Anyway.

766
00:55:00,800 --> 00:55:02,080
Hope these will be enough.

767
00:55:03,000 --> 00:55:04,120
Should be.

768
00:55:15,480 --> 00:55:16,760
She's late.

769
00:55:24,240 --> 00:55:26,600
The person you have called cannot be reached at the moment.

770
00:55:29,400 --> 00:55:30,400
Her phone is off.

771
00:55:34,320 --> 00:55:35,640
Did something happen?

772
00:55:41,200 --> 00:55:43,800
I should go to the company.

773
00:55:47,360 --> 00:55:48,360
Where are you going?

774
00:55:49,160 --> 00:55:50,280
I cannot reach Mercan.

775
00:55:50,640 --> 00:55:51,760
I'll check the company.

776
00:55:52,600 --> 00:55:54,320
Mercan is not at the company.

777
00:55:54,520 --> 00:55:56,120
I saw her entering a restaurant.

778
00:55:58,560 --> 00:55:59,560
Restaurant?

779
00:55:59,920 --> 00:56:00,920
What's she doing there?

780
00:56:01,960 --> 00:56:03,160
How should I know?

781
00:56:05,160 --> 00:56:06,160
Was she alone?

782
00:56:06,840 --> 00:56:07,880
Yes, I saw only her.

783
00:56:08,560 --> 00:56:10,360
Who knows what she is up to again.

784
00:56:12,960 --> 00:56:14,040
Which restaurant?

785
00:56:15,560 --> 00:56:18,960
You know the one near to the company buıilding?

786
00:56:19,960 --> 00:56:20,960
Okay.

787
00:56:31,120 --> 00:56:32,600
Son, stop dragging it.

788
00:56:32,760 --> 00:56:33,800
Who paid the debt?

789
00:56:34,080 --> 00:56:35,080
Gosh.

790
00:56:35,320 --> 00:56:36,640
You still insist?

791
00:56:37,720 --> 00:56:38,880
You misunderstood me.

792
00:56:39,360 --> 00:56:42,160
I did not say I know. My tongue slipped.

793
00:56:42,400 --> 00:56:44,799
You are a terrible liar, brother.

794
00:56:44,800 --> 00:56:47,720
It is obvious. Just say it.

795
00:56:50,960 --> 00:56:51,640
It is late.

796
00:56:51,641 --> 00:56:53,441
I will check the automatic irrigation system.

797
00:56:54,320 --> 00:56:55,320
Sit there.

798
00:56:55,520 --> 00:56:57,760
You are not leaving until you answer.

799
00:57:03,080 --> 00:57:04,760
Enough is enough, just say it.

800
00:57:07,760 --> 00:57:08,760
Alright.

801
00:57:09,320 --> 00:57:10,320
I will say.

802
00:57:11,000 --> 00:57:12,000
Malik paid it.

803
00:57:46,160 --> 00:57:47,160
Is it not working?

804
00:57:48,760 --> 00:57:50,200
It must be broken.

805
00:57:51,560 --> 00:57:52,280
I am sorry.

806
00:57:52,400 --> 00:57:54,440
I will buy you a phone tomorrow.

807
00:57:55,320 --> 00:57:56,320
Not needed.

808
00:57:56,360 --> 00:57:57,360
It will work.

809
00:57:58,080 --> 00:57:59,680
Let us wait, maybe it can work again.

810
00:58:02,560 --> 00:58:04,440
Looks like he won't come.

811
00:58:05,040 --> 00:58:06,200
I should leave.

812
00:58:06,280 --> 00:58:07,920
Let me call again first.

813
00:58:24,720 --> 00:58:26,400
Alright, got it.

814
00:58:29,760 --> 00:58:30,760
What did he say?

815
00:58:33,440 --> 00:58:33,960
Don't ask.

816
00:58:34,120 --> 00:58:35,200
They had an accident.

817
00:58:36,000 --> 00:58:37,000
Oh God.

818
00:58:38,400 --> 00:58:39,680
Thank God nothing serious.

819
00:58:39,760 --> 00:58:41,480
We will postpone the meeting.

820
00:58:42,280 --> 00:58:44,080
I dragged you here as well. Sorry.

821
00:58:46,000 --> 00:58:47,000
Let us go then.

822
00:58:48,080 --> 00:58:49,080
I'm starving.

823
00:58:50,120 --> 00:58:52,600
Since we're here, let us eat.

824
00:58:53,320 --> 00:58:55,280
This way, I can apologize for this situation.

825
00:58:55,720 --> 00:58:56,400
Not needed.

826
00:58:56,600 --> 00:58:58,520
I really want to go.

827
00:58:59,120 --> 00:59:01,120
Ok but can you give me two minutes of your time?

828
00:59:01,520 --> 00:59:03,040
I want to show you something.

829
00:59:36,000 --> 00:59:37,000
Bought it for Demet.

830
00:59:43,200 --> 00:59:44,560
But not sure yet.

831
00:59:44,840 --> 00:59:47,080
Just wanted your opinion as well.

832
01:00:10,280 --> 01:00:11,360
Just her style.

833
01:00:12,480 --> 01:00:13,600
I'm sure she'll love it.

834
01:00:23,720 --> 01:00:26,480
Could I... // try this on you?

835
01:00:26,640 --> 01:00:28,400
To see how it looks.

836
01:00:29,640 --> 01:00:34,640
If it puts your mind at ease, try it.

837
01:01:31,280 --> 01:01:32,280
How is it?

838
01:03:38,440 --> 01:03:40,920
You do not deserve anything.

839
01:03:48,400 --> 01:03:50,400
That gesture you made for Demet was thoughtful.

840
01:03:50,880 --> 01:03:51,880
She will be thrilled.

841
01:03:53,680 --> 01:03:55,520
That is what being an older brother calls for.

842
01:03:56,240 --> 01:03:58,960
Do not be fooled, I have a gentle side too.

843
01:04:03,520 --> 01:04:05,440
You must be in pieces now, Mr. Ateş.

844
01:04:39,600 --> 01:04:41,800
You will probably add a nice note inside as well.

845
01:04:44,760 --> 01:04:45,760
Of course I will.

846
01:04:46,120 --> 01:04:47,559
I need to go now.

847
01:04:47,560 --> 01:04:49,640
My dinner offer still stands.

848
01:04:50,080 --> 01:04:51,480
We came all this way anyway.

849
01:04:51,880 --> 01:04:54,440
No, I really have to go, Nezir.

850
01:04:54,680 --> 01:04:55,680
Thanks.

851
01:05:02,560 --> 01:05:03,880
Sorry about that, Mercan.

852
01:05:05,800 --> 01:05:06,800
You will be mine.

853
01:05:07,280 --> 01:05:08,280
One way or another.

854
01:06:02,680 --> 01:06:04,200
How dare you touch her?

855
01:06:05,720 --> 01:06:07,280
What are you trying to do?

856
01:07:23,200 --> 01:07:24,200
Are you okay?

857
01:07:24,640 --> 01:07:25,640
What happened here?

858
01:07:30,000 --> 01:07:31,080
Get out of here.

859
01:07:34,200 --> 01:07:35,920
Looks like all hell broke loose.

860
01:07:56,320 --> 01:07:57,520
This is my favorite movie.

861
01:08:36,520 --> 01:08:39,960
I... I do not understand. Are you going to tell me what happened?

862
01:08:40,960 --> 01:08:43,280
I told you to leave the room.

863
01:08:46,040 --> 01:08:47,320
Look, I truly do not understand.

864
01:08:49,000 --> 01:08:50,000
What happened?

865
01:08:51,040 --> 01:08:52,560
Why... why did you do this?

866
01:08:57,120 --> 01:08:58,120
Where?

867
01:08:59,000 --> 01:09:00,000
Where what?

868
01:09:00,080 --> 01:09:01,536
I do not even understand what you are looking at.

869
01:09:01,560 --> 01:09:02,560
Say it.

870
01:09:04,200 --> 01:09:05,200
Of course not.

871
01:09:05,400 --> 01:09:06,400
She hid it.

872
01:09:07,240 --> 01:09:09,400
Why are you asking like you care?

873
01:09:12,320 --> 01:09:13,560
Of course I care.

874
01:09:14,120 --> 01:09:15,800
It is obvious you prepared something.

875
01:09:16,800 --> 01:09:17,800
But then...

876
01:09:24,320 --> 01:09:25,760
What is the point of all this drama?

877
01:09:35,080 --> 01:09:36,360
You and him...

878
01:10:25,240 --> 01:10:26,360
I had prepared it, yes.

879
01:10:28,640 --> 01:10:29,760
But I changed my mind.

880
01:10:35,000 --> 01:10:37,960
Turns out there was no need to do anything for you.

881
01:10:40,240 --> 01:10:41,800
You were not worth it.

882
01:10:46,480 --> 01:10:47,480
Why?

883
01:10:50,040 --> 01:10:52,480
Because you lost the innocent child inside you.

884
01:10:56,440 --> 01:10:57,600
I thought it was still there.

885
01:11:07,800 --> 01:11:08,800
I was mistaken.

886
01:11:28,000 --> 01:11:29,376
I am telling you for the last time.

887
01:11:29,400 --> 01:11:30,400
Get out of here.

888
01:11:52,200 --> 01:11:53,520
Get a grip on yourself.

889
01:13:52,200 --> 01:13:53,879
Back in our day, young people were

890
01:13:53,880 --> 01:13:57,760
shy to tell their loved ones, their husbands, that they loved them.

891
01:13:58,080 --> 01:14:01,240
There was no habit of going out to buy gifts either.

892
01:14:01,440 --> 01:14:02,880
We made things with our own labor...

893
01:14:03,800 --> 01:14:06,759
Sometimes stitch by stitch with our love,

894
01:14:06,760 --> 01:14:08,960
sometimes needle by needle.

895
01:14:11,200 --> 01:14:12,359
Otherwise you would put your name to it...

896
01:14:12,360 --> 01:14:16,680
Malik, why did you not say you paid our debt?

897
01:14:20,240 --> 01:14:22,680
Well, it was not important.

898
01:14:22,880 --> 01:14:24,640
Not even worth talking about.

899
01:14:24,680 --> 01:14:26,119
I left my work unfinished, I should go.

900
01:14:26,120 --> 01:14:27,680
Hold on, come here.

901
01:14:30,520 --> 01:14:32,680
Where are you going without answering that question?

902
01:14:38,000 --> 01:14:39,800
I told you, Aunt Binnaz.

903
01:14:40,120 --> 01:14:41,120
It was nothing important.

904
01:14:41,640 --> 01:14:43,080
These kinds of helping hands happen.

905
01:14:43,680 --> 01:14:44,680
No need to talk about it.

906
01:14:45,120 --> 01:14:47,680
Today me, tomorrow Berat takes turn.

907
01:14:48,680 --> 01:14:49,920
Is that not right, my brother?

908
01:14:50,040 --> 01:14:51,040
My dear brother.

909
01:14:51,400 --> 01:14:53,200
Oh my sweet brother.

910
01:14:54,200 --> 01:14:55,536
This is how a decent young man behaves.

911
01:14:55,560 --> 01:14:57,839
You see, these things happen between men.

912
01:14:57,840 --> 01:15:00,440
Support, help in hard times.

913
01:15:00,520 --> 01:15:01,520
Quiet now.

914
01:15:03,240 --> 01:15:05,320
When mothers are speaking, you do not get a word in.

915
01:15:08,560 --> 01:15:10,719
Malik, my son, alright, thank you.

916
01:15:10,720 --> 01:15:12,639
May God bless you for paying this debt.

917
01:15:12,640 --> 01:15:15,000
But where did you find that much money, son?

918
01:15:15,120 --> 01:15:17,040
How did you clear such a mountain of debt?

919
01:15:19,400 --> 01:15:20,400
For a rainy day.

920
01:15:20,720 --> 01:15:22,120
My brother.

921
01:15:22,480 --> 01:15:23,959
What kind of bad day was that supposed to be?

922
01:15:23,960 --> 01:15:25,840
You would have to be hit by seven calamities...

923
01:15:29,440 --> 01:15:30,680
Alright, Malik.

924
01:15:31,080 --> 01:15:34,040
If you say so, then so be it.

925
01:15:34,280 --> 01:15:35,640
But listen, a debt is a debt.

926
01:15:36,520 --> 01:15:38,919
I have never owed anyone in my life.

927
01:15:38,920 --> 01:15:40,440
I will not start today either.

928
01:15:40,960 --> 01:15:43,799
We will pay you back, son.

929
01:15:43,800 --> 01:15:44,800
That is final.

930
01:15:46,480 --> 01:15:47,480
Yes, yes, Malik.

931
01:15:48,960 --> 01:15:50,520
I am not saying anything different.

932
01:15:50,720 --> 01:15:51,720
We will pay it back.

933
01:15:51,760 --> 01:15:53,000
I said we would already.

934
01:15:53,040 --> 01:15:54,416
Did I not say it, my brother, we will pay it back.

935
01:15:54,440 --> 01:15:56,600
We are not the kind to sit on someone else’s money.

936
01:15:57,560 --> 01:15:59,040
Please, there is no need.

937
01:15:59,280 --> 01:16:00,280
Let the matter be closed.

938
01:16:00,520 --> 01:16:01,600
No, Malik.

939
01:16:02,200 --> 01:16:03,200
No.

940
01:16:03,760 --> 01:16:06,360
I have never owed anyone, son.

941
01:16:07,360 --> 01:16:11,240
Every bite I have eaten came from my own labor.

942
01:16:11,640 --> 01:16:14,000
Otherwise my heart would not be at ease.

943
01:16:14,440 --> 01:16:15,440
I could not stomach it.

944
01:16:15,560 --> 01:16:17,240
We will pay you back, son.

945
01:16:19,120 --> 01:16:20,280
Alright. Alright, Aunt Binnaz.

946
01:16:20,520 --> 01:16:23,120
If that will put your mind at ease, let us do it that way.

947
01:16:29,440 --> 01:16:30,960
That scarf...

948
01:16:31,960 --> 01:16:34,280
I already left my work unfinished.

949
01:16:34,480 --> 01:16:35,480
I should go.

950
01:16:36,040 --> 01:16:37,040
Move.

951
01:16:39,160 --> 01:16:40,800
Such a decent boy.

952
01:16:41,680 --> 01:16:42,880
Truly a decent boy.

953
01:16:43,120 --> 01:16:43,880
Look, Malik...

954
01:16:43,960 --> 01:16:45,216
Berat, get out from under my feet...

955
01:16:45,240 --> 01:16:46,360
slipper is coming your way.

956
01:16:47,640 --> 01:16:48,960
You, I swear...

957
01:16:50,120 --> 01:16:51,120
Mom.

958
01:16:52,200 --> 01:16:52,960
God forbid.

959
01:16:52,961 --> 01:16:55,040
Go on, girl, get my shoes too.

960
01:16:57,080 --> 01:16:59,520
She is still off defending Malik to me.

961
01:16:59,920 --> 01:17:00,960
I brought them, mom.

962
01:17:09,040 --> 01:17:10,160
You have worn me out.

963
01:17:12,600 --> 01:17:15,280
We will talk about that scarf later, my girl.

964
01:17:19,480 --> 01:17:20,680
Do not think I did not notice.

965
01:17:22,880 --> 01:17:24,760
At my age, they turned me into a plaything.

966
01:17:58,640 --> 01:18:00,680
A surprise was prepared for me.

967
01:18:06,560 --> 01:18:08,080
Then why did he cancel it?

968
01:18:12,960 --> 01:18:15,440
Something must have happened again and I have no idea.

969
01:18:16,800 --> 01:18:19,560
Otherwise why would he tear apart the surprise he prepared himself?

970
01:18:21,600 --> 01:18:23,840
Why did he get so angry?

971
01:18:45,400 --> 01:18:47,040
If only I knew what happened.

972
01:18:47,640 --> 01:18:48,640
If only I knew.

973
01:19:34,080 --> 01:19:38,120
Because you lost the innocent child inside you.

974
01:19:46,680 --> 01:19:48,520
Why did you say that to me?

975
01:19:50,160 --> 01:19:51,160
Why?

976
01:20:47,440 --> 01:20:48,480
Are you okay?

977
01:20:53,440 --> 01:20:55,640
If you have calmed down, shall we talk for a bit?

978
01:21:03,840 --> 01:21:05,920
Where did you hide that bracelet?

979
01:21:17,280 --> 01:21:18,520
There is nothing to talk about.

980
01:21:21,440 --> 01:21:22,880
You got angry about something again.

981
01:21:23,720 --> 01:21:25,920
And as always, I have no idea why.

982
01:21:28,920 --> 01:21:29,920
Please tell me.

983
01:21:30,920 --> 01:21:32,720
Why did you build those walls of anger again?

984
01:21:37,040 --> 01:21:39,240
You cannot do this without telling me what is going on.

985
01:21:39,560 --> 01:21:40,640
You are not going anywhere.

986
01:21:47,200 --> 01:21:49,840
Do you think you can stop me?

987
01:21:51,000 --> 01:21:52,960
You know I can.

988
01:21:59,440 --> 01:22:00,680
Do not cross your line.

989
01:22:04,720 --> 01:22:06,000
You are a Karahan.

990
01:22:16,880 --> 01:22:18,200
What do you mean, line?

991
01:22:19,640 --> 01:22:20,680
What do you mean, Karahan?

992
01:22:22,440 --> 01:22:23,600
You think about that.

993
01:22:29,800 --> 01:22:31,200
I have some work to do.

994
01:23:02,080 --> 01:23:04,360
I will wait until you talk to me.

995
01:23:04,760 --> 01:23:05,760
Here.

996
01:23:05,800 --> 01:23:07,800
This is your secret hideout after all.

997
01:23:08,400 --> 01:23:09,640
Then keep waiting.

998
01:23:10,280 --> 01:23:12,000
I am going to the office.

999
01:23:12,760 --> 01:23:13,760
Be here when I get back.

1000
01:23:24,600 --> 01:23:27,120
I am not asking you a question, alright?

1001
01:23:27,520 --> 01:23:29,960
If you talk, then it will be as if I never asked.

1002
01:23:31,680 --> 01:23:32,920
I cannot understand you.

1003
01:23:33,960 --> 01:23:35,880
You keep everything inside, it is exhausting.

1004
01:23:36,000 --> 01:23:36,680
That is how I am.

1005
01:23:36,681 --> 01:23:39,640
I just want to solve whatever the problem is by talking.

1006
01:23:40,640 --> 01:23:42,080
I do not want to talk.

1007
01:23:42,360 --> 01:23:44,480
And if there is a problem, I do not want to solve it.

1008
01:23:56,640 --> 01:23:58,720
You even tore up the movie poster.

1009
01:24:06,120 --> 01:24:07,240
Why will you not talk?

1010
01:24:09,160 --> 01:24:10,160
Patience.

1011
01:24:11,640 --> 01:24:15,160
What part of “I do not want to talk” do you not understand?

1012
01:24:16,640 --> 01:24:17,120
I understand.

1013
01:24:17,121 --> 01:24:19,480
I just refuse to accept it.

1014
01:24:20,600 --> 01:24:21,600
That is your problem.

1015
01:24:22,360 --> 01:24:23,360
Yes, it is my problem.

1016
01:24:25,880 --> 01:24:29,440
Whatever happened to you, in that room, is it not about me?

1017
01:24:35,560 --> 01:24:36,800
I am coming too.

1018
01:25:05,080 --> 01:25:06,400
You cannot keep doing this to me.

1019
01:25:07,480 --> 01:25:09,160
You cannot leave me in the dark like this.

1020
01:25:30,320 --> 01:25:31,320
Hello, mom?

1021
01:25:32,080 --> 01:25:33,080
How are you?

1022
01:25:33,240 --> 01:25:35,560
Is everything alright?

1023
01:25:36,720 --> 01:25:37,720
Is everything alright?

1024
01:25:37,840 --> 01:25:39,640
Habibi, my son.

1025
01:25:41,000 --> 01:25:42,320
You said you were coming.

1026
01:25:42,800 --> 01:25:43,800
What happened? Yes, mom.

1027
01:25:44,800 --> 01:25:46,520
But I need a bit more time.

1028
01:25:47,600 --> 01:25:48,120
I will come.

1029
01:25:48,320 --> 01:25:49,720
I just need some more time.

1030
01:25:50,480 --> 01:25:52,400
You are afraid of your father.

1031
01:25:53,120 --> 01:25:55,480
Do not worry about him, son.

1032
01:25:55,600 --> 01:25:58,160
He misses you too.

1033
01:25:58,520 --> 01:25:59,520
He does not show it.

1034
01:25:59,720 --> 01:26:01,680
When you come, you will see, you will make peace.

1035
01:26:02,640 --> 01:26:03,360
I do not know.

1036
01:26:03,440 --> 01:26:04,440
I do not know, mom.

1037
01:26:04,640 --> 01:26:05,800
But you are very optimistic.

1038
01:26:06,440 --> 01:26:07,800
The man disowned me.

1039
01:26:08,920 --> 01:26:10,240
In the end, he disowned me.

1040
01:26:10,400 --> 01:26:11,080
God forbid.

1041
01:26:11,280 --> 01:26:12,800
It is not disowning, son.

1042
01:26:13,600 --> 01:26:14,840
Your father wanted...

1043
01:26:15,080 --> 01:26:16,576
his only son to take over the company.

1044
01:26:16,600 --> 01:26:17,920
And you packed up and left.

1045
01:26:18,560 --> 01:26:20,760
Your leaving hurt him.

1046
01:26:21,920 --> 01:26:22,920
Anyway. Anyway, mom.

1047
01:26:23,200 --> 01:26:24,400
I will stay here a bit longer.

1048
01:26:25,000 --> 01:26:26,000
Alright?

1049
01:26:26,920 --> 01:26:28,360
I will be around for a while longer.

1050
01:26:28,440 --> 01:26:32,280
What an endless school this is, my son. We missed you so much.

1051
01:26:32,360 --> 01:26:36,080
You keep stalling me, son.

1052
01:26:36,560 --> 01:26:38,200
We missed you so much.

1053
01:26:38,560 --> 01:26:39,560
We were wondering.

1054
01:26:39,960 --> 01:26:42,160
Or did you fall in love, Malik?

1055
01:26:43,320 --> 01:26:44,639
Mom, never mind.

1056
01:26:44,640 --> 01:26:45,936
I have some work, we will talk later.

1057
01:26:45,960 --> 01:26:46,960
Alright?

1058
01:26:48,040 --> 01:26:49,680
Alright, talk to you later. Bye.

1059
01:26:51,600 --> 01:26:52,600
Malik. My Çiçek?

1060
01:26:54,200 --> 01:26:56,680
Why didn't you tell me you were the one who paid the debt?

1061
01:26:57,880 --> 01:26:58,880
Well...

1062
01:27:00,560 --> 01:27:02,240
I could not tell you, Çiçek.

1063
01:27:02,320 --> 01:27:03,480
How was I supposed to say it?

1064
01:27:03,720 --> 01:27:06,160
Besides, if I had, Aunt Binnaz might not have accepted it.

1065
01:27:07,640 --> 01:27:09,320
What matters is the issue was resolved.

1066
01:27:09,600 --> 01:27:11,216
Please let us not talk about this anymore.

1067
01:27:11,240 --> 01:27:13,120
No, Malik, this is different.

1068
01:27:13,880 --> 01:27:15,440
You hid something from me.

1069
01:27:15,720 --> 01:27:17,400
Was trust not supposed to be so important?

1070
01:27:17,640 --> 01:27:20,920
So you get to keep secrets and I do not, is that it?

1071
01:27:21,080 --> 01:27:22,159
No, of course not.

1072
01:27:22,160 --> 01:27:23,216
That is not what this is about.

1073
01:27:23,240 --> 01:27:25,639
But money matters...

1074
01:27:25,640 --> 01:27:27,456
Talking about them would have been improper, Çiçek.

1075
01:27:27,480 --> 01:27:28,480
That is why.

1076
01:27:28,481 --> 01:27:30,800
No matter what, you should have told me.

1077
01:27:32,080 --> 01:27:33,360
Alright, you are right.

1078
01:27:34,360 --> 01:27:37,680
Look, I see you all as my family.

1079
01:27:38,800 --> 01:27:40,480
You do everything for family.

1080
01:27:42,840 --> 01:27:43,840
Alright then.

1081
01:27:44,360 --> 01:27:45,360
Thank you.

1082
01:27:45,840 --> 01:27:47,800
But if we are family, there should be no secrets.

1083
01:27:50,040 --> 01:27:53,480
And tell me, where did you find that much money?

1084
01:27:54,000 --> 01:27:56,959
You did not go asking loan sharks like my brother, did you?

1085
01:27:56,960 --> 01:27:58,520
No, Çiçek.

1086
01:27:59,280 --> 01:28:00,536
Would I ever do something like that?

1087
01:28:00,560 --> 01:28:01,560
For God’s sake.

1088
01:28:01,680 --> 01:28:04,480
I told you, I had some savings put aside.

1089
01:28:04,840 --> 01:28:05,840
That is all.

1090
01:28:07,160 --> 01:28:08,160
Alright.

1091
01:28:08,880 --> 01:28:10,080
But I will say one thing.

1092
01:28:10,760 --> 01:28:11,640
Aunt Binnaz was looking at me very...

1093
01:28:11,641 --> 01:28:13,160
strangely.

1094
01:28:13,840 --> 01:28:14,840
Really?

1095
01:28:15,640 --> 01:28:16,920
Do you think she figured us out?

1096
01:28:18,320 --> 01:28:19,320
No way.

1097
01:28:20,360 --> 01:28:21,360
Did she?

1098
01:28:24,400 --> 01:28:25,799
No, no, she did not.

1099
01:28:25,800 --> 01:28:29,800
She is fixated on that debt, that is why it felt that way.

1100
01:28:31,520 --> 01:28:36,880
And I have no tolerance left for anything coming between us.

1101
01:28:39,040 --> 01:28:41,680
Neither do I, my Çiçek, none at all.

1102
01:28:45,640 --> 01:28:46,800
Someone will see.

1103
01:28:48,520 --> 01:28:52,480
♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪ ARABIC DIALOG ♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪♪

1104
01:28:53,080 --> 01:28:53,840
So what?

1105
01:28:53,841 --> 01:28:56,360
If they see, let them see.

1106
01:28:56,720 --> 01:29:02,200
Let them see and know how much I love you.

1107
01:29:19,160 --> 01:29:20,920
Good morning, Mr. Ateş.

1108
01:29:21,120 --> 01:29:22,120
Good morning.

1109
01:29:25,880 --> 01:29:27,760
There is definitely something going on again.

1110
01:29:27,840 --> 01:29:29,880
No, as if we ever have a quiet day around here.

1111
01:29:34,840 --> 01:29:35,920
Good morning, Ms. Mercan.

1112
01:29:39,920 --> 01:29:41,856
Something happened between them, something is off.

1113
01:29:41,880 --> 01:29:42,240
What happened?

1114
01:29:42,560 --> 01:29:44,080
Everyone, back to work.

1115
01:29:44,280 --> 01:29:45,336
There is nothing to watch here. Move along.

1116
01:29:45,360 --> 01:29:46,360
Disperse.

1117
01:29:50,640 --> 01:29:53,680
Both of them are on fire.

1118
01:29:53,760 --> 01:29:55,720
Looks like the movie did not have a happy ending.

1119
01:29:56,680 --> 01:29:58,960
Insallah, for the best.

1120
01:30:00,720 --> 01:30:02,120
This is not about work, Ms. Zahide.

1121
01:30:02,520 --> 01:30:04,720
There are things more important than work in this life.

1122
01:30:04,840 --> 01:30:06,280
Did you two make it official?

1123
01:30:07,920 --> 01:30:09,800
Do you think you can run away from me?

1124
01:30:11,120 --> 01:30:12,320
I am not in the mood to chat.

1125
01:30:12,760 --> 01:30:13,760
I am, though.

1126
01:30:18,800 --> 01:30:19,800
Out.

1127
01:30:21,080 --> 01:30:22,080
I am not leaving.

1128
01:30:22,760 --> 01:30:24,040
Try me if you want.

1129
01:30:25,000 --> 01:30:26,000
Patience.

1130
01:30:27,320 --> 01:30:28,920
Get as annoyed as you like.

1131
01:30:29,480 --> 01:30:31,759
I am sick of these unknowns too,

1132
01:30:31,760 --> 01:30:33,360
of these outbursts I do not understand.

1133
01:30:33,960 --> 01:30:35,400
First you prepare a surprise.

1134
01:30:37,400 --> 01:30:39,360
Thank you, that was very thoughtful.

1135
01:30:39,760 --> 01:30:41,720
Then you tear everything down.

1136
01:30:42,200 --> 01:30:44,680
You act like I did something terrible.

1137
01:30:45,680 --> 01:30:46,680
Did you not?

1138
01:30:47,040 --> 01:30:48,120
What did I do?

1139
01:30:48,600 --> 01:30:50,080
What did I do to make you this angry?

1140
01:30:50,920 --> 01:30:53,320
Excuse me, but I should be the one angry.

1141
01:30:54,720 --> 01:30:57,720
You text me saying the surprise is canceled and gave no explanation at all.

1142
01:30:58,640 --> 01:30:59,640
I said fine.

1143
01:30:59,680 --> 01:31:01,000
There must be a reason, but...

1144
01:31:01,440 --> 01:31:03,080
Hold on, wait a second.

1145
01:31:06,960 --> 01:31:08,320
I did not send you any message.

1146
01:31:09,680 --> 01:31:10,760
How did you not?

1147
01:31:12,080 --> 01:31:14,240
I was all ready to leave.

1148
01:31:14,360 --> 01:31:17,280
Then you wrote that the meeting was canceled.

1149
01:31:17,440 --> 01:31:18,480
Sure, I got bored.

1150
01:31:18,640 --> 01:31:21,480
I did not send you a message like that.

1151
01:31:23,840 --> 01:31:24,840
How did you not?

1152
01:31:25,720 --> 01:31:26,720
You did.

1153
01:31:27,080 --> 01:31:30,160
I do not remember the exact time, but it was around seven.

1154
01:31:30,560 --> 01:31:32,560
Alright, if I sent it, show me.

1155
01:31:34,240 --> 01:31:35,240
I cannot.

1156
01:31:35,600 --> 01:31:38,480
Water spilled on my phone yesterday, it will not turn on now.

1157
01:31:43,120 --> 01:31:45,560
Well, would you look at that.

1158
01:31:45,960 --> 01:31:46,960
It will not turn on.

1159
01:31:49,080 --> 01:31:51,120
I would be surprised if I believed you.

1160
01:31:54,840 --> 01:31:55,920
Then you open yours.

1161
01:31:56,320 --> 01:31:57,800
You are the one who sent the message.

1162
01:32:08,440 --> 01:32:09,440
Here, take a look.

1163
01:32:10,880 --> 01:32:13,040
Did I send it or not?

1164
01:32:16,920 --> 01:32:17,920
How is that possible?

1165
01:32:22,200 --> 01:32:23,480
I have had enough of this talk.

1166
01:32:23,880 --> 01:32:24,520
I have work to do.

1167
01:32:24,560 --> 01:32:25,560
Get out now.

1168
01:32:26,280 --> 01:32:28,720
I saw the message with my own eyes.

1169
01:32:29,120 --> 01:32:30,560
There is something fishy about this.

1170
01:32:31,760 --> 01:32:32,760
Well, well.

1171
01:32:39,720 --> 01:32:41,000
Why would I lie to you?

1172
01:32:42,320 --> 01:32:44,120
You sent me that message.

1173
01:32:45,320 --> 01:32:46,720
I told you to get out.

1174
01:32:48,800 --> 01:32:49,800
I am not leaving.

1175
01:32:50,600 --> 01:32:51,600
Is that so?

1176
01:32:51,760 --> 01:32:52,760
It is.

1177
01:32:56,560 --> 01:32:57,560
What are you doing?

1178
01:32:58,760 --> 01:33:00,040
Put me down, what are you doing?

1179
01:33:03,640 --> 01:33:05,000
Put me down.

1180
01:33:06,160 --> 01:33:07,280
People are watching.

1181
01:33:24,960 --> 01:33:25,960
Ateş.

1182
01:33:27,760 --> 01:33:28,760
Please.

1183
01:33:29,200 --> 01:33:30,200
I am so embarrassed.

1184
01:33:32,560 --> 01:33:33,720
Put me down.

1185
01:33:40,240 --> 01:33:41,240
Put me down!

1186
01:34:05,720 --> 01:34:07,040
What did you just do?

1187
01:34:09,760 --> 01:34:11,120
Get in and leave.

1188
01:34:13,400 --> 01:34:15,600
I do not want to see your face for a while.

1189
01:34:19,440 --> 01:34:20,800
You will not get rid of me.

1190
01:34:21,320 --> 01:34:23,440
I will get the phone fixed and show you that message.

1191
01:34:46,280 --> 01:34:47,640
I wish there were such a message.

1192
01:34:48,520 --> 01:34:49,600
I wish I could believe you.

1193
01:34:51,360 --> 01:34:52,360
Where are you, Nezir?

1194
01:34:53,560 --> 01:34:54,800
Where are you, you damn man?

1195
01:35:04,400 --> 01:35:05,520
Where is my money?

1196
01:35:06,120 --> 01:35:07,120
We lost the stones.

1197
01:35:07,600 --> 01:35:09,840
We will not get a dime out of Mr. Ateş after this point.

1198
01:35:10,000 --> 01:35:10,880
Mercan will not even look me in the eye.

1199
01:35:10,920 --> 01:35:12,320
I came out of this the worst off.

1200
01:35:12,880 --> 01:35:14,320
You will pay the money we agreed on.

1201
01:35:16,000 --> 01:35:17,320
You know how partnerships work.

1202
01:35:18,160 --> 01:35:19,640
When we win, we both win.

1203
01:35:20,040 --> 01:35:21,760
When we lose, we both lose.

1204
01:35:22,840 --> 01:35:24,640
We are in the same boat, do not forget that.

1205
01:35:24,960 --> 01:35:28,600
Then you will throw the rats on that boat overboard and pay me my money.

1206
01:35:29,200 --> 01:35:31,320
If you do not pay, I will tell Mercan everything.

1207
01:35:31,720 --> 01:35:32,720
Did you hear me?

1208
01:35:33,320 --> 01:35:34,320
Alright.

1209
01:35:34,440 --> 01:35:35,560
You will get your money.

1210
01:35:35,680 --> 01:35:36,680
And then some.

1211
01:35:39,760 --> 01:35:40,760
I will, of course.

1212
01:35:41,560 --> 01:35:42,560
But do not drag this out.

1213
01:36:18,720 --> 01:36:19,720
Well, well.

1214
01:36:20,720 --> 01:36:22,200
I wonder who dropped this.

1215
01:36:25,120 --> 01:36:26,320
What key is this, anyway?

1216
01:36:37,440 --> 01:36:39,320
We really botched the movie night business.

1217
01:36:39,840 --> 01:36:43,960
As if the lady were a princess and that room was meant for cinema nights.

1218
01:36:46,000 --> 01:36:49,000
Everyone lives what they deserve.

1219
01:36:49,240 --> 01:36:51,320
Especially when we are the ones handing out justice.

1220
01:36:52,320 --> 01:36:53,440
But the war is not over.

1221
01:36:56,680 --> 01:36:59,760
We fight on until Haydar’s last fortress falls.

1222
01:37:01,600 --> 01:37:04,800
The more Ateş drifts off course, the more we need to pull him back in.

1223
01:37:09,960 --> 01:37:11,160
Yes, Ms. Handan.

1224
01:37:15,600 --> 01:37:16,880
The documents for the candidacy.

1225
01:37:17,640 --> 01:37:18,640
Yes, I understand.

1226
01:37:22,400 --> 01:37:25,400
I will send them to the foundation’s address with the boys.

1227
01:37:27,280 --> 01:37:28,280
What candidacy?

1228
01:37:30,440 --> 01:37:34,560
The people at the foundation insisted I run for president.

1229
01:37:35,040 --> 01:37:37,160
I could not turn them down, so I put my name forward.

1230
01:37:37,840 --> 01:37:39,320
That is why all the paperwork.

1231
01:37:45,120 --> 01:37:47,080
Who would insist on you, anyway?

1232
01:37:48,800 --> 01:37:50,440
As if you were some rare treasure.

1233
01:38:01,880 --> 01:38:05,280
You must have been lobbying behind closed doors for the presidency.

1234
01:38:10,720 --> 01:38:11,720
But wait.

1235
01:38:12,880 --> 01:38:15,240
That job is not so easy, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

1236
01:38:19,560 --> 01:38:21,960
Still, the presidency would suit you.

1237
01:38:22,840 --> 01:38:25,160
I am always by your side, in everything.

1238
01:38:26,040 --> 01:38:28,080
Leadership fits your aura.

1239
01:38:28,480 --> 01:38:29,760
My dear girl.

1240
01:39:17,160 --> 01:39:20,680
You text saying the surprise is canceled and give no explanation at all.

1241
01:39:26,360 --> 01:39:27,360
Do not come.

1242
01:39:32,840 --> 01:39:34,360
Well, well, Ateş Karahan.

1243
01:39:34,680 --> 01:39:35,720
So this is who we are now?

1244
01:39:37,160 --> 01:39:38,200
Sorry, Cemal.

1245
01:39:38,560 --> 01:39:39,560
Come.

1246
01:39:43,840 --> 01:39:45,040
That is why I came anyway.

1247
01:39:46,440 --> 01:39:47,800
Everywhere you step turns to fire.

1248
01:39:48,200 --> 01:39:49,200
Calm down a little.

1249
01:39:52,400 --> 01:39:55,360
Anyone watching would think something serious is going on between you two.

1250
01:39:55,640 --> 01:39:57,600
Cemal, I don't want to break your heart.

1251
01:40:02,760 --> 01:40:04,120
Alright, fair enough.

1252
01:40:08,160 --> 01:40:09,640
If I do not ask, it will eat at me.

1253
01:40:10,880 --> 01:40:12,280
If I do, I know you will get angry.

1254
01:40:15,320 --> 01:40:17,040
But clearly something went wrong yesterday.

1255
01:40:21,160 --> 01:40:22,480
This time my anger is not at her.

1256
01:40:23,720 --> 01:40:24,720
It is at myself.

1257
01:40:25,440 --> 01:40:29,000
Between films and all that, we took courtesy too far.

1258
01:40:29,960 --> 01:40:30,800
Things got out of hand.

1259
01:40:30,801 --> 01:40:32,321
No, come on, what do you mean too far?

1260
01:40:32,960 --> 01:40:33,960
Even if we did, so what.

1261
01:40:34,040 --> 01:40:35,040
We are human, after all.

1262
01:40:35,160 --> 01:40:36,640
It is not a matter of life and death.

1263
01:40:37,440 --> 01:40:39,000
Sometimes we stumble and fall.

1264
01:40:39,760 --> 01:40:41,440
And we know how to get back up, evelallah.

1265
01:40:45,120 --> 01:40:46,400
We have been together for years.

1266
01:40:46,840 --> 01:40:49,160
You know better than anyone how much I have stumbled.

1267
01:40:52,480 --> 01:40:53,840
And every time, you had my back.

1268
01:40:54,880 --> 01:40:56,440
So do not be so hard on yourself.

1269
01:41:02,840 --> 01:41:03,840
Thanks, Cemal.

1270
01:41:06,240 --> 01:41:08,360
If one day I lose my way...

1271
01:41:10,160 --> 01:41:13,600
do not forget to warn me, alright?

1272
01:41:15,360 --> 01:41:16,520
That is what friends are for.

1273
01:41:20,760 --> 01:41:22,920
But lately, you have been stumbling a lot.

1274
01:41:23,240 --> 01:41:25,080
At this rate, you will outdo me.

1275
01:42:06,880 --> 01:42:08,120
How were things at the mansion?

1276
01:42:08,640 --> 01:42:09,680
Did the storm break loose?

1277
01:42:10,760 --> 01:42:12,680
The storms broke loose.

1278
01:42:13,000 --> 01:42:14,280
The lightning struck too.

1279
01:42:15,240 --> 01:42:18,000
Everything was ruined just the way we wanted.

1280
01:42:18,400 --> 01:42:19,400
Good.

1281
01:42:20,040 --> 01:42:22,280
Mr. Ateş intended to host a movie night, but...

1282
01:42:22,960 --> 01:42:24,600
we were the ones who made the real film.

1283
01:42:26,680 --> 01:42:29,480
In their eyes now, Mercan is a woman who deceived Ateş.

1284
01:42:33,560 --> 01:42:37,040
Everything is fine, but... why is this man still so quiet?

1285
01:42:37,920 --> 01:42:39,440
He should have been in my face by now.

1286
01:42:40,840 --> 01:42:42,800
He probably has nothing left to say.

1287
01:42:43,000 --> 01:42:44,760
He has already done with Mercan in his head.

1288
01:42:46,800 --> 01:42:47,920
Maybe.

1289
01:42:51,200 --> 01:42:52,240
But listen, Aslı...

1290
01:42:54,280 --> 01:42:55,280
It should not end here.

1291
01:42:56,000 --> 01:42:57,160
We should shoot a sequel too.

1292
01:42:59,880 --> 01:43:01,040
I am ready.

1293
01:43:04,680 --> 01:43:10,200
But... not a hair on Mercan’s head will be harmed.

1294
01:43:12,160 --> 01:43:14,960
As long as not a hair on Ateş’s head is harmed...

1295
01:43:16,040 --> 01:43:17,040
that works for me too.

1296
01:43:23,640 --> 01:43:24,800
Deal.

1297
01:43:25,480 --> 01:43:26,480
Deal.

1298
01:43:34,040 --> 01:43:36,280
What was all that hoisting onto the shoulder about?

1299
01:43:39,680 --> 01:43:40,680
He is crazy, that is all.

1300
01:43:42,840 --> 01:43:43,840
Well, well.

1301
01:43:44,600 --> 01:43:48,000
It is strange he won't even admit sending the cancellation message, is it not?

1302
01:43:49,480 --> 01:43:51,960
When it comes to him, nothing surprises me anymore, Demet.

1303
01:43:53,160 --> 01:43:55,279
In our case, it is not oddities but normalcy

1304
01:43:55,280 --> 01:43:57,360
that would be newsworthy by now.

1305
01:43:58,200 --> 01:44:00,040
So what will you do?

1306
01:44:01,480 --> 01:44:03,160
I will do what I always do.

1307
01:44:04,440 --> 01:44:05,440
I will not give up.

1308
01:44:08,480 --> 01:44:09,640
I gave the phone to Yaşar.

1309
01:44:09,840 --> 01:44:11,440
He will get it fixed and bring it to me.

1310
01:44:11,640 --> 01:44:13,360
Then I will show that message to Ateş.

1311
01:44:16,240 --> 01:44:17,240
No...

1312
01:44:17,600 --> 01:44:19,320
It feels like that is not really the point.

1313
01:44:20,520 --> 01:44:22,200
I mean, him blowing it up this much...

1314
01:44:23,040 --> 01:44:24,920
I do not know, he must have been waiting.

1315
01:44:25,560 --> 01:44:28,120
And when you did not come...

1316
01:44:28,200 --> 01:44:30,240
Like you said, did he really lose his mind?

1317
01:44:33,320 --> 01:44:35,160
It hurts me deeply, Demet.

1318
01:44:35,480 --> 01:44:36,919
I have no idea what is going on...

1319
01:44:36,920 --> 01:44:39,360
yet the whole world is crashing down on me.

1320
01:44:39,920 --> 01:44:41,760
He accuses me of lying, can you believe it?

1321
01:44:45,160 --> 01:44:47,240
If he does not believe I am telling the truth...

1322
01:44:48,120 --> 01:44:49,560
then I will prove myself.

1323
01:44:56,600 --> 01:44:57,600
What is it?

1324
01:44:59,600 --> 01:45:03,080
Some things are coming to mind but...

1325
01:45:04,280 --> 01:45:07,480
I do not know whether I should say it or not.

1326
01:45:09,720 --> 01:45:10,880
What is it, say it.

1327
01:45:12,600 --> 01:45:13,600
Ateş...

1328
01:45:14,760 --> 01:45:16,640
Hosting movie nights and all that.

1329
01:45:18,120 --> 01:45:20,040
Did that stone heart finally soften?

1330
01:45:21,240 --> 01:45:24,160
Or is something else stirring in the heart we thought was stone?

1331
01:45:26,720 --> 01:45:27,960
What do you mean?

1332
01:45:32,400 --> 01:45:33,400
No.

1333
01:45:33,840 --> 01:45:34,960
Where would that heart go?

1334
01:45:37,320 --> 01:45:39,000
It is a rock, not even stone.

1335
01:45:39,840 --> 01:45:41,680
I do not even know how it ever cracks.

1336
01:45:42,840 --> 01:45:48,880
All he knows is... bark orders... sit, stand... get in, get out...

1337
01:45:57,680 --> 01:45:59,480
By the way, that bracelet looks great on you.

1338
01:45:59,880 --> 01:46:01,400
Thank you, my brother bought it.

1339
01:46:02,320 --> 01:46:03,320
Yes.

1340
01:46:03,440 --> 01:46:05,080
I saw it, Nezir showed it yesterday.

1341
01:46:05,920 --> 01:46:07,360
I liked it a lot too.

1342
01:46:10,720 --> 01:46:13,120
What do you say, shall we have a coffee on the terrace?

1343
01:46:14,520 --> 01:46:15,520
Sure.

1344
01:46:15,560 --> 01:46:17,320
Alright, let me use the restroom first.

1345
01:46:17,560 --> 01:46:18,800
Then we meet, alright?

1346
01:46:19,080 --> 01:46:20,080
Okay, dear.

1347
01:46:25,480 --> 01:46:27,440
Hosting movie nights and all that.

1348
01:46:29,320 --> 01:46:30,880
Did that stone heart finally soften?

1349
01:46:32,040 --> 01:46:35,480
Or is something else stirring in the heart we thought was stone?

1350
01:46:56,880 --> 01:46:57,880
What are you doing?

1351
01:47:00,560 --> 01:47:02,479
Before you hurt yourself...

1352
01:47:02,480 --> 01:47:04,280
I am taking you upstairs.

1353
01:47:31,800 --> 01:47:32,800
No.

1354
01:47:33,440 --> 01:47:34,560
No, impossible.

1355
01:47:36,400 --> 01:47:37,400
This is Ateş Karahan.

1356
01:47:37,480 --> 01:47:38,480
That does not happen.

1357
01:48:02,040 --> 01:48:04,920
Where is this scarf?

1358
01:48:08,840 --> 01:48:10,480
Search properly now.

1359
01:48:14,760 --> 01:48:17,720
Oh Çiçek, oh Çiçek.

1360
01:48:37,280 --> 01:48:39,080
Where could you have put it?

1361
01:48:39,560 --> 01:48:40,560
Ms. Çiçek.

1362
01:48:48,800 --> 01:48:49,800
Where could it be?

1363
01:48:50,320 --> 01:48:51,320
Did you put it here?

1364
01:48:52,160 --> 01:48:53,160
Not here.

1365
01:48:53,320 --> 01:48:54,320
Let's check the bottom.

1366
01:48:56,520 --> 01:48:57,520
No.

1367
01:48:58,680 --> 01:49:01,560
Did this girl really knit this scarf...

1368
01:49:02,080 --> 01:49:03,640
Oh dear...

1369
01:49:08,440 --> 01:49:11,280
What if she really knit this scarf... for Malik?

1370
01:49:12,600 --> 01:49:14,000
Oh dear, oh dear.

1371
01:49:30,320 --> 01:49:31,320
Where could it be?

1372
01:49:38,920 --> 01:49:40,720
Did you break up with your boyfriend?

1373
01:49:40,920 --> 01:49:42,000
What is with that face?

1374
01:49:44,960 --> 01:49:45,960
No.

1375
01:49:46,120 --> 01:49:47,480
I do not have a boyfriend.

1376
01:49:48,120 --> 01:49:48,640
No, dear.

1377
01:49:48,800 --> 01:49:50,360
If I did, I would know.

1378
01:49:50,600 --> 01:49:51,600
No.

1379
01:49:52,400 --> 01:49:55,200
If your daughter had a boyfriend, you would be the last to know.

1380
01:49:55,680 --> 01:49:57,240
Young people hide their hearts

1381
01:49:57,960 --> 01:50:00,720
from their mothers.

1382
01:50:02,120 --> 01:50:06,480
But the heart always finds a way to speak.

1383
01:50:11,440 --> 01:50:12,440
God help us.

1384
01:50:15,200 --> 01:50:17,560
Could it be that they really...

1385
01:50:17,760 --> 01:50:19,560
right under our noses...

1386
01:50:20,240 --> 01:50:21,560
before my very eyes...

1387
01:50:23,440 --> 01:50:24,440
No.

1388
01:50:25,680 --> 01:50:26,280
No, dear.

1389
01:50:26,560 --> 01:50:27,560
No. It cannot be.

1390
01:50:28,480 --> 01:50:29,760
Çiçek would not do such a thing.

1391
01:50:30,760 --> 01:50:31,880
Malik would not either.

1392
01:50:32,360 --> 01:50:33,360
He is a decent boy.

1393
01:50:33,840 --> 01:50:34,960
Of course. I have to find it.

1394
01:50:35,560 --> 01:50:36,560
Where did she put it?

1395
01:50:39,440 --> 01:50:40,840
Do not say impossible, Binnaz.

1396
01:50:41,320 --> 01:50:43,120
Do not say impossible, do not drop this.

1397
01:50:43,480 --> 01:50:45,480
In this life, the impossible happens all the time.

1398
01:50:46,560 --> 01:50:50,000
I need to go and shed light on this, I need to find out.

1399
01:51:12,080 --> 01:51:13,080
Come here.

1400
01:51:16,960 --> 01:51:18,360
Yes, just like that.

1401
01:51:21,920 --> 01:51:22,920
Come here.

1402
01:51:23,560 --> 01:51:24,680
I told you to come here.

1403
01:51:38,680 --> 01:51:39,840
Yes, what did you need?

1404
01:51:42,320 --> 01:51:44,760
What is the status of the Ankara Project files?

1405
01:51:46,800 --> 01:51:48,720
The progress reports are almost done.

1406
01:51:49,840 --> 01:51:52,040
I want them in my office before the end of the workday.

1407
01:51:52,600 --> 01:51:52,960
Alright.

1408
01:51:53,480 --> 01:51:55,720
Bring the company’s latest financial statements as well.

1409
01:51:57,120 --> 01:51:58,120
Alright.

1410
01:51:58,640 --> 01:51:59,960
I will tell Yaşar to bring them.

1411
01:52:01,160 --> 01:52:03,720
If I wanted Yaşar, I would have told Yaşar.

1412
01:52:05,640 --> 01:52:06,640
You will bring them.

1413
01:52:07,360 --> 01:52:08,640
And one more thing...

1414
01:52:09,360 --> 01:52:10,960
First bring me a black Turkish coffee.

1415
01:52:13,680 --> 01:52:14,720
With sugar?

1416
01:52:15,760 --> 01:52:16,760
Very sugary.

1417
01:52:21,880 --> 01:52:22,960
You know I drink it black.

1418
01:52:24,520 --> 01:52:25,720
Black, like me.

1419
01:52:27,000 --> 01:52:29,880
Of course, you probably mix sugar into your coffee, do you not?

1420
01:52:30,680 --> 01:52:31,680
God forbid.

1421
01:52:32,160 --> 01:52:32,880
How was I supposed to know?

1422
01:52:32,920 --> 01:52:34,200
Maybe you changed your mind.

1423
01:52:36,320 --> 01:52:38,159
I do not change my preferences easily.

1424
01:52:38,160 --> 01:52:39,160
Are you sure?

1425
01:52:40,120 --> 01:52:41,760
Do you not change your mind all the time?

1426
01:52:42,280 --> 01:52:45,520
Like preparing a movie night and then dropping it all of a sudden, for example.

1427
01:52:46,320 --> 01:52:47,560
How about focusing on work now?

1428
01:52:48,760 --> 01:52:50,160
That movie thing is over for me.

1429
01:52:50,800 --> 01:52:51,880
That topic is closed.

1430
01:52:58,400 --> 01:52:59,000
You say work.

1431
01:52:59,320 --> 01:53:00,320
Good reminder, actually.

1432
01:53:01,120 --> 01:53:03,480
Do you not keep changing the limits of the contract too?

1433
01:53:04,800 --> 01:53:05,800
I do not.

1434
01:53:07,920 --> 01:53:09,800
Take another look at the contract if you want.

1435
01:53:10,960 --> 01:53:12,320
You do not have a job description.

1436
01:53:13,240 --> 01:53:15,840
It only says you work directly under me.

1437
01:53:16,200 --> 01:53:19,360
So if I say report, it is a report. If I say coffee, it is coffee.

1438
01:53:20,120 --> 01:53:21,560
And as black as it gets.

1439
01:53:29,560 --> 01:53:31,320
Why do you keep staring at my wrists?

1440
01:53:32,640 --> 01:53:33,840
Are you looking for something?

1441
01:53:34,280 --> 01:53:36,280
Stop stalling, get back to work.

1442
01:53:39,880 --> 01:53:40,880
Drama king.

1443
01:53:41,320 --> 01:53:42,320
Did you say something?

1444
01:53:44,320 --> 01:53:45,320
I said drama king.

1445
01:54:01,120 --> 01:54:02,519
And what does Demet go and say?

1446
01:54:02,520 --> 01:54:05,040
If there is anything in his heart, it is stone.

1447
01:54:06,080 --> 01:54:07,480
I know you are talking to yourself.

1448
01:54:12,600 --> 01:54:13,840
Then know what I am saying too.

1449
01:54:19,960 --> 01:54:21,080
Come on, do not stand there.

1450
01:54:21,720 --> 01:54:22,720
And bring some water too.

1451
01:54:25,360 --> 01:54:26,760
Alright, I am going.

1452
01:54:27,800 --> 01:54:30,400
Since you are burning inside so much, I will bring you water too.

1453
01:54:30,680 --> 01:54:32,360
And a coffee with lots of sugar.

1454
01:54:33,240 --> 01:54:34,240
Black.

1455
01:54:35,840 --> 01:54:36,840
Exactly.

1456
01:54:53,320 --> 01:54:55,400
You must have forgotten to knock.

1457
01:54:55,880 --> 01:54:57,720
I honestly do not remember much.

1458
01:54:58,880 --> 01:55:00,240
You will remember next time.

1459
01:55:02,200 --> 01:55:03,200
Here you go.

1460
01:55:03,440 --> 01:55:04,440
Extra sugar.

1461
01:55:04,520 --> 01:55:04,920
Sorry.

1462
01:55:05,520 --> 01:55:06,240
I could not remember that either.

1463
01:55:06,360 --> 01:55:07,560
Was it supposed to be plain?

1464
01:55:08,440 --> 01:55:10,160
And here is your water, ice cold.

1465
01:55:10,400 --> 01:55:11,400
Just like you.

1466
01:55:12,920 --> 01:55:14,200
One of the reports is ready.

1467
01:55:15,320 --> 01:55:17,320
The other will be ready by the end of the workday.

1468
01:55:18,400 --> 01:55:19,840
Thank you, you may go.

1469
01:55:20,720 --> 01:55:22,040
Thank you very much.

1470
01:55:22,360 --> 01:55:24,400
If you need anything else, I will be in my office.

1471
01:55:24,720 --> 01:55:26,800
If I do, I will let you know, do not worry.

1472
01:55:42,560 --> 01:55:45,800
I came thinking we would look over the files and have a chat.

1473
01:55:47,520 --> 01:55:48,520
What is going on?

1474
01:55:49,000 --> 01:55:50,480
You seem unusually tense today.

1475
01:55:50,600 --> 01:55:51,600
Mr. Ateş?

1476
01:55:52,640 --> 01:55:54,080
I am not in the best mood, Aslı.

1477
01:55:56,120 --> 01:55:57,720
You are right about Mercan.

1478
01:55:58,720 --> 01:56:00,640
That girl feels like she has a hidden agenda.

1479
01:56:01,720 --> 01:56:05,920
Especially lately... she is always hanging around with Nezir.

1480
01:56:08,360 --> 01:56:11,880
Either they are up to something... or...

1481
01:56:13,320 --> 01:56:15,840
Anyway, that is not our concern.

1482
01:56:16,040 --> 01:56:17,640
It is their private business, after all.

1483
01:56:29,760 --> 01:56:31,320
My head is messy today, Aslı.

1484
01:56:32,680 --> 01:56:34,200
We can look at those files later.

1485
01:56:35,040 --> 01:56:35,600
Alright.

1486
01:56:35,840 --> 01:56:37,160
As long as you feel better.

1487
01:56:37,680 --> 01:56:39,120
We can deal with them later.

1488
01:56:39,560 --> 01:56:40,560
Alright.

1489
01:56:41,640 --> 01:56:43,680
How about we go out for dinner tonight, you and me?

1490
01:56:44,120 --> 01:56:45,320
To clear your head.

1491
01:56:52,200 --> 01:56:54,840
Mr. Ateş, I am sorry, I could not stop him.

1492
01:56:55,400 --> 01:56:56,400
You go outside.

1493
01:56:59,160 --> 01:57:00,240
Aslı, you too.

1494
01:57:13,120 --> 01:57:14,240
We are going to talk.

1495
01:57:16,320 --> 01:57:17,800
You got my message.

1496
01:57:20,480 --> 01:57:21,680
Do not say I did not warn you.

1497
01:57:23,440 --> 01:57:25,440
If you enter my office without permission again...

1498
01:57:28,360 --> 01:57:30,120
the consequences will be very heavy for you.

1499
01:57:31,200 --> 01:57:33,399
If I ever enter your office again...

1500
01:57:33,400 --> 01:57:34,520
then you can do that.

1501
01:57:34,600 --> 01:57:35,720
But this place is not yours.

1502
01:57:36,680 --> 01:57:38,120
The house you live in is not yours.

1503
01:57:38,680 --> 01:57:39,800
Mercan is not yours.

1504
01:57:40,480 --> 01:57:43,160
You only seized everything through a deal.

1505
01:57:43,440 --> 01:57:44,520
But only for a while.

1506
01:57:46,000 --> 01:57:47,640
When the time comes, you will get lost.

1507
01:57:49,120 --> 01:57:50,560
So if you do not know your limits...

1508
01:57:58,840 --> 01:58:01,240
You are the last person who gets to lecture me about limits.

1509
01:58:02,920 --> 01:58:04,480
You said your piece.

1510
01:58:06,000 --> 01:58:07,000
I have work to do.

1511
01:58:08,520 --> 01:58:10,040
Get out before I throw you out myself.

1512
01:58:11,840 --> 01:58:14,080
I will take back everything you seized from me.

1513
01:58:16,240 --> 01:58:18,600
One by one... piece by piece...

1514
01:58:21,560 --> 01:58:24,160
This company... the house...

1515
01:58:25,240 --> 01:58:27,280
Even everything you care about.

1516
01:58:33,960 --> 01:58:35,960
I told Mercan the same thing at dinner yesterday.

1517
01:58:36,560 --> 01:58:38,040
I am ready to do anything for her.

1518
01:58:40,080 --> 01:58:41,200
We were at dinner yesterday.

1519
01:58:41,840 --> 01:58:43,280
You must know that by now.

1520
01:58:52,120 --> 01:58:54,560
Do you know what the biggest difference between us, Nezir?

1521
01:58:56,280 --> 01:58:58,120
While you are making one plan...

1522
01:58:58,840 --> 01:59:00,400
I am making ten.

1523
01:59:02,160 --> 01:59:03,840
While you are running drenched in sweat...

1524
01:59:05,400 --> 01:59:08,280
I am lapping you on one leg.

1525
01:59:10,560 --> 01:59:12,240
Do not try to measure yourself against me.

1526
01:59:12,960 --> 01:59:14,000
You are out of your depth.

1527
01:59:16,240 --> 01:59:19,400
Mr. Ateş... you are underestimating me.

1528
01:59:20,680 --> 01:59:21,680
Naturally.

1529
01:59:23,640 --> 01:59:25,000
In a fight, punches do not count.

1530
01:59:27,120 --> 01:59:29,000
Challenge accepted!

1531
01:59:30,160 --> 01:59:31,200
Challenge accepted.

1532
01:59:48,440 --> 01:59:50,760
I will take back everything you seized from me.

1533
01:59:51,040 --> 01:59:53,520
One by one... piece by piece...

1534
01:59:54,040 --> 01:59:56,560
this company... the house...

1535
01:59:56,800 --> 01:59:58,120
Even everything you care about.

1536
02:00:11,360 --> 02:00:13,480
Let it go now so others can work too.

1537
02:00:13,600 --> 02:00:14,680
Look, I brought you coffee.

1538
02:00:14,920 --> 02:00:16,040
Oh, I cannot say no to that.

1539
02:00:17,040 --> 02:00:18,560
We are doing a really good job though.

1540
02:00:19,440 --> 02:00:21,200
We have become quite the duo, have we not?

1541
02:00:21,640 --> 02:00:22,400
Yes.

1542
02:00:22,600 --> 02:00:25,520
Work carried out in harmony always brings good results.

1543
02:00:25,920 --> 02:00:27,760
That is why harmony matters.

1544
02:00:28,080 --> 02:00:29,760
In fact, harmony is everything.

1545
02:00:38,560 --> 02:00:40,240
I have some work to do.

1546
02:00:40,440 --> 02:00:41,720
I should go.

1547
02:00:44,520 --> 02:00:45,520
What is going on?

1548
02:00:47,560 --> 02:00:48,560
Who is this?

1549
02:00:49,840 --> 02:00:50,320
Brother...

1550
02:00:50,800 --> 02:00:51,800
Burak...

1551
02:00:51,840 --> 02:00:54,200
A colleague we worked with for the hospital.

1552
02:00:55,360 --> 02:00:57,120
He is supporting our work with Mercan.

1553
02:00:58,440 --> 02:00:59,760
I did not like the look his eyes.

1554
02:01:01,400 --> 02:01:02,400
I have my eye on him.

1555
02:01:30,760 --> 02:01:33,280
Let us see where you are going, Ms. Çiçek.

1556
02:01:36,280 --> 02:01:38,760
What schemes are you running behind my back, we will find out.

1557
02:01:40,200 --> 02:01:41,840
Could she be meeting Malik?

1558
02:01:42,840 --> 02:01:44,280
Either way, we will know soon.

1559
02:02:05,920 --> 02:02:06,920
So?

1560
02:02:09,080 --> 02:02:10,200
Where did she go?

1561
02:02:11,360 --> 02:02:15,160
This way or that way?

1562
02:02:18,160 --> 02:02:20,080
How did this girl vanish in two steps?

1563
02:02:24,240 --> 02:02:26,200
You are really funny.

1564
02:02:26,720 --> 02:02:28,480
That is what they say, Zehra dear, you know.

1565
02:02:29,080 --> 02:02:33,160
By the way, girls do not fall for men who make them laugh, do they?

1566
02:02:33,320 --> 02:02:34,600
Yes, that is right.

1567
02:02:35,200 --> 02:02:36,400
Well, well.

1568
02:02:36,880 --> 02:02:38,200
Where did this girl disappear to?

1569
02:02:42,160 --> 02:02:44,240
Did I come to the meeting spot?

1570
02:02:45,040 --> 02:02:47,440
Am I about to catch my own daughter?

1571
02:02:47,920 --> 02:02:49,400
Oh, the things that happen to me.

1572
02:02:49,920 --> 02:02:50,640
God help me.

1573
02:02:50,920 --> 02:02:52,176
I am like this by nature anyway.

1574
02:02:52,200 --> 02:02:55,200
My real dream, no, my real life is exactly like this.

1575
02:02:56,960 --> 02:02:57,960
Oh dear...

1576
02:03:00,600 --> 02:03:02,480
Oh dear, we came fishing for anchovies,

1577
02:03:02,600 --> 02:03:03,640
and mackerel bit the hook.

1578
02:03:05,160 --> 02:03:07,360
What business does my son have with this doe-eyed one?

1579
02:03:16,920 --> 02:03:18,960
Mother dear, I would not die like that.

1580
02:03:19,120 --> 02:03:20,200
Pull the trigger and shoot.

1581
02:03:22,480 --> 02:03:23,720
You will not die anyway.

1582
02:03:24,040 --> 02:03:25,240
First, you will answer for it.

1583
02:03:28,400 --> 02:03:29,720
What are you doing here?

1584
02:03:40,520 --> 02:03:41,520
We are having tea.

1585
02:05:59,280 --> 02:06:00,520
So you are saying keep going?

1586
02:06:04,320 --> 02:06:05,600
I like continuity.

1587
02:06:06,120 --> 02:06:07,120
It shows consistency.

1588
02:06:08,640 --> 02:06:10,000
Keep up the sulking, the attitude.

1589
02:06:11,000 --> 02:06:12,560
Fine, do not tell me anything.

1590
02:06:12,880 --> 02:06:14,480
Live on your own like this.

1591
02:06:19,840 --> 02:06:21,440
Do you care about me that much?

1592
02:06:24,200 --> 02:06:25,480
Clearly there is a problem.

1593
02:06:26,080 --> 02:06:27,280
I am only curious.

1594
02:06:27,760 --> 02:06:30,440
We solve it or we do not, but at least we talk, right?

1595
02:06:32,200 --> 02:06:34,400
How much longer will this attitude of yours last?

1596
02:06:36,640 --> 02:06:38,136
We have been through so much together.

1597
02:06:38,160 --> 02:06:39,560
We cheated death.

1598
02:06:39,920 --> 02:06:41,440
We finally started talking properly.

1599
02:06:42,760 --> 02:06:45,080
Then suddenly, everything went back to square one.

1600
02:06:46,360 --> 02:06:47,360
What is going on?

1601
02:06:50,240 --> 02:06:52,160
If only I had never mentioned that movie to you.

1602
02:06:54,800 --> 02:06:56,640
If only you had never made those preparations.

1603
02:06:58,040 --> 02:07:00,279
If only you had not torn everything you prepared to pieces.

1604
02:07:00,280 --> 02:07:01,280
If only...

1605
02:07:03,080 --> 02:07:05,080
You make me say too many if onlys.

1606
02:07:05,840 --> 02:07:09,280
Did you say "if only" after you promised me and gone to dinner with Nezir?

1607
02:07:10,640 --> 02:07:12,840
Or for that bracelet you accepted as a gift.

1608
02:07:14,360 --> 02:07:15,440
What are you talking about?

1609
02:07:15,920 --> 02:07:16,920
What bracelet?

1610
02:07:18,160 --> 02:07:19,160
I was there.

1611
02:07:19,640 --> 02:07:20,640
I saw it.

1612
02:07:32,800 --> 02:07:33,800
So where is it?

1613
02:07:35,000 --> 02:07:36,520
You are not even wearing the bracelet.

1614
02:07:38,160 --> 02:07:40,440
You looked very happy.

1615
02:07:40,960 --> 02:07:42,120
Your eyes were shining.

1616
02:07:51,840 --> 02:07:52,840
But you are a Karahan.

1617
02:07:54,520 --> 02:07:55,520
You are my wife.

1618
02:08:02,440 --> 02:08:04,520
You were there?

1619
02:08:05,680 --> 02:08:07,760
If you were there, why did you not come to me?

1620
02:08:08,480 --> 02:08:09,480
You know, I am your wife.

1621
02:08:11,920 --> 02:08:14,600
You... did you think that bracelet was for me?

1622
02:08:16,880 --> 02:08:19,000
I cannot believe this, is this why all this behavior?

1623
02:08:21,600 --> 02:08:22,760
What did you expect me to do?

1624
02:08:23,680 --> 02:08:25,720
Just ask. That simple.

1625
02:08:26,320 --> 02:08:27,840
That bracelet was not for me.

1626
02:08:28,320 --> 02:08:29,680
It was not for you.

1627
02:08:30,160 --> 02:08:31,520
Then why was he showing it to you?

1628
02:08:34,880 --> 02:08:36,320
Always a lie, always something.

1629
02:08:38,480 --> 02:08:39,680
You never listen.

1630
02:08:40,000 --> 02:08:41,000
You never listen.

1631
02:08:41,600 --> 02:08:43,159
You have already convinced yourself of something

1632
02:08:43,160 --> 02:08:44,880
and you question me only through that.

1633
02:08:46,200 --> 02:08:47,320
I do question you.

1634
02:08:48,720 --> 02:08:50,160
You are my wife.

1635
02:08:51,040 --> 02:08:52,280
You carry my last name.

1636
02:09:00,040 --> 02:09:03,200
My wife does not dine with other men.

1637
02:09:04,520 --> 02:09:05,560
She does not accept gifts.

1638
02:09:09,960 --> 02:09:10,960
I get it, alright.

1639
02:09:11,320 --> 02:09:12,520
I am talking to a wall.

1640
02:09:14,080 --> 02:09:15,400
But you remember this too.

1641
02:09:16,520 --> 02:09:17,880
This will be over in a few months.

1642
02:09:18,680 --> 02:09:20,640
We will never see each other again.

1643
02:09:23,120 --> 02:09:24,840
You and me.

1644
02:09:25,480 --> 02:09:28,200
We are nothing but a clause in a written agreement.

1645
02:09:29,240 --> 02:09:31,000
That is what you always said, remember?

1646
02:09:39,720 --> 02:09:40,840
You are pushing my patience.

1647
02:09:42,520 --> 02:09:43,520
Do not push it.

1648
02:09:44,800 --> 02:09:47,080
I did nothing to disgrace you.

1649
02:09:48,000 --> 02:09:49,840
But you keep calling me your wife.

1650
02:09:50,240 --> 02:09:51,320
You are the one pushing me.

1651
02:10:07,200 --> 02:10:09,160
Why are you being so possessive?

1652
02:10:11,640 --> 02:10:14,440
